78static inline bool cv_isalnum(char c)
79{
80 return ('0' <= c && c <= '9') || ('a' <= c && c <= 'z') || ('A' <= c && c <= 'Z');
81}
82
83static inline bool cv_isalpha(char c)
84{
85 return ('a' <= c && c <= 'z') || ('A' <= c && c <= 'Z');
86}
87
88static inline bool cv_isdigit(char c)
89{
90 return '0' <= c && c <= '9';
91}
92
93static inline bool cv_isspace(char c)
94{
95 return (9 <= c && c <= 13) || c == ' ';
96}

98static char* icv_itoa( int _val, char* buffer, int /*radix*/ )
99{
100 const int radix = 10;
101 char* ptr=buffer + 23 /* enough even for 64-bit integers */;
102 unsigned val = abs(_val);
103
104 *ptr = '\0';
105 do
106 {
107 unsigned r = val / radix;
108 *--ptr = (char)(val - (r*radix) + '0');
109 val = r;
110 }
111 while( val != 0 );
112
113 if( _val < 0 )
114 *--ptr = '-';
115
116 return ptr;
117}

119cv::string cv::FileStorage::getDefaultObjectName(const string& _filename)
120{
121 static const char* stubname = "unnamed";
122 const char* filename = _filename.c_str();
123 const char* ptr2 = filename + _filename.size();
124 const char* ptr = ptr2 - 1;
125 cv::AutoBuffer<char> name_buf(_filename.size()+1);
126
127 while( ptr >= filename && *ptr != '\\' && *ptr != '/' && *ptr != ':' )
128 {
129 if( *ptr == '.' && (!*ptr2 || strncmp(ptr2, ".gz", 3) == 0) )
130 ptr2 = ptr;
131 ptr--;
132 }
133 ptr++;
134 if( ptr == ptr2 )
135 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Invalid filename" );
136
137 char* name = name_buf;
138
139 // name must start with letter or '_'
140 if( !cv_isalpha(*ptr) && *ptr!= '_' ){
141 *name++ = '_';
142 }
143
144 while( ptr < ptr2 )
145 {
146 char c = *ptr++;
147 if( !cv_isalnum(c) && c != '-' && c != '_' )
148 c = '_';
149 *name++ = c;
150 }
151 *name = '\0';
152 name = name_buf;
153 if( strcmp( name, "_" ) == 0 )
154 strcpy( name, stubname );
155 return cv::string(name);
156}

161string fromUtf16(const WString& str)
162{
163 cv::AutoBuffer<char> _buf(str.size()*4 + 1);
164 char* buf = _buf;
165
166 size_t sz = wcstombs(buf, str.c_str(), str.size());
167 if( sz == (size_t)-1 )
168 return string();
169 buf[sz] = '\0';
170 return string(buf);
171}

173WString toUtf16(const string& str)
174{
175 cv::AutoBuffer<wchar_t> _buf(str.size() + 1);
176 wchar_t* buf = _buf;
177
178 size_t sz = mbstowcs(buf, str.c_str(), str.size());
179 if( sz == (size_t)-1 )
180 return WString();
181 buf[sz] = '\0';
182 return WString(buf);
183}

275static void icvPuts( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* str )
276{
277 if( fs->outbuf )
278 std::copy(str, str + strlen(str), std::back_inserter(*fs->outbuf));
279 else if( fs->file )
280 fputs( str, fs->file );
281#if USE_ZLIB
282 else if( fs->gzfile )
283 gzputs( fs->gzfile, str );
284#endif
285 else
286 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The storage is not opened" );
287}
288
289static char* icvGets( CvFileStorage* fs, char* str, int maxCount )
290{
291 if( fs->strbuf )
292 {
293 size_t i = fs->strbufpos, len = fs->strbufsize;
294 int j = 0;
295 const char* instr = fs->strbuf;
296 while( i < len && j < maxCount-1 )
297 {
298 char c = instr[i++];
299 if( c == '\0' )
300 break;
301 str[j++] = c;
302 if( c == '\n' )
303 break;
304 }
305 str[j++] = '\0';
306 fs->strbufpos = i;
307 return j > 1 ? str : 0;
308 }
309 if( fs->file )
310 return fgets( str, maxCount, fs->file );
311#if USE_ZLIB
312 if( fs->gzfile )
313 return gzgets( fs->gzfile, str, maxCount );
314#endif
315 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The storage is not opened" );
316 return 0;
317}

319static int icvEof( CvFileStorage* fs )
320{
321 if( fs->strbuf )
322 return fs->strbufpos >= fs->strbufsize;
323 if( fs->file )
324 return feof(fs->file);
325#if USE_ZLIB
326 if( fs->gzfile )
327 return gzeof(fs->gzfile);
328#endif
329 return false;
330}

332static void icvCloseFile( CvFileStorage* fs )
333{
334 if( fs->file )
335 fclose( fs->file );
336#if USE_ZLIB
337 else if( fs->gzfile )
338 gzclose( fs->gzfile );
339#endif
340 fs->file = 0;
341 fs->gzfile = 0;
342 fs->strbuf = 0;
343 fs->strbufpos = 0;
344 fs->is_opened = false;
345}

347static void icvRewind( CvFileStorage* fs )
348{
349 if( fs->file )
350 rewind(fs->file);
351#if USE_ZLIB
352 else if( fs->gzfile )
353 gzrewind(fs->gzfile);
354#endif
355 fs->strbufpos = 0;
356}

380CV_IMPL const char*
381cvAttrValue( const CvAttrList* attr, const char* attr_name )
382{
383 while( attr && attr->attr )
384 {
385 int i;
386 for( i = 0; attr->attr[i*2] != 0; i++ )
387 {
388 if( strcmp( attr_name, attr->attr[i*2] ) == 0 )
389 return attr->attr[i*2+1];
390 }
391 attr = attr->next;
392 }
393
394 return 0;
395}

398static CvGenericHash*
399cvCreateMap( int flags, int header_size, int elem_size,
400 CvMemStorage* storage, int start_tab_size )
401{
402 if( header_size < (int)sizeof(CvGenericHash) )
403 CV_Error( CV_StsBadSize, "Too small map header_size" );
404
405 if( start_tab_size <= 0 )
406 start_tab_size = 16;
407
408 CvGenericHash* map = (CvGenericHash*)cvCreateSet( flags, header_size, elem_size, storage );
409
410 map->tab_size = start_tab_size;
411 start_tab_size *= sizeof(map->table[0]);
412 map->table = (void**)cvMemStorageAlloc( storage, start_tab_size );
413 memset( map->table, 0, start_tab_size );
414
415 return map;
416}

421static void
422icvParseError( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* func_name,
423 const char* err_msg, const char* source_file, int source_line )
424{

431static void
432icvFSCreateCollection( CvFileStorage* fs, int tag, CvFileNode* collection )
433{
434 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(tag) )
435 {
436 if( collection->tag != CV_NODE_NONE )
437 {
438 assert( fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML );
439 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Sequence element should not have name (use <_></_>)" );
440 }
441
442 collection->data.map = cvCreateMap( 0, sizeof(CvFileNodeHash),
443 sizeof(CvFileMapNode), fs->memstorage, 16 );
444 }
445 else
446 {
447 CvSeq* seq;
448 seq = cvCreateSeq( 0, sizeof(CvSeq), sizeof(CvFileNode), fs->memstorage );
449
450 // if <collection> contains some scalar element, add it to the newly created collection
451 if( CV_NODE_TYPE(collection->tag) != CV_NODE_NONE )
452 cvSeqPush( seq, collection );
453
454 collection->data.seq = seq;
455 }
456
457 collection->tag = tag;
458 cvSetSeqBlockSize( collection->data.seq, 8 );
459}

489static char*
490icvFSDoResize( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, int len )
491{
492 char* new_ptr = 0;
493 int written_len = (int)(ptr - fs->buffer_start);
494 int new_size = (int)((fs->buffer_end - fs->buffer_start)*3/2);
495 new_size = MAX( written_len + len, new_size );
496 new_ptr = (char*)cvAlloc( new_size + 256 );
497 fs->buffer = new_ptr + (fs->buffer - fs->buffer_start);
498 if( written_len > 0 )
499 memcpy( new_ptr, fs->buffer_start, written_len );
500 fs->buffer_start = new_ptr;
501 fs->buffer_end = fs->buffer_start + new_size;
502 new_ptr += written_len;
503 return new_ptr;
504}
505
506
507inline char* icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, int len )
508{
509 return ptr + len < fs->buffer_end ? ptr : icvFSDoResize( fs, ptr, len );
510}

513static char*
514icvFSFlush( CvFileStorage* fs )
515{
516 char* ptr = fs->buffer;
517 int indent;
518
519 if( ptr > fs->buffer_start + fs->space )
520 {
521 ptr[0] = '\n';
522 ptr[1] = '\0';
523 icvPuts( fs, fs->buffer_start );
524 fs->buffer = fs->buffer_start;
525 }
526
527 indent = fs->struct_indent;
528
529 if( fs->space != indent )
530 {
531 if( fs->space < indent )
532 memset( fs->buffer_start + fs->space, ' ', indent - fs->space );
533 fs->space = indent;
534 }
535
536 ptr = fs->buffer = fs->buffer_start + fs->space;
537
538 return ptr;
539}

542static void
543icvClose( CvFileStorage* fs, std::string* out )
544{
545 if( out )
546 out->clear();
547
548 if( !fs )
549 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "NULL double pointer to file storage" );
550
551 if( fs->is_opened )
552 {
553 if( fs->write_mode && (fs->file || fs->gzfile || fs->outbuf) )
554 {
555 if( fs->write_stack )
556 {
557 while( fs->write_stack->total > 0 )
558 cvEndWriteStruct(fs);
559 }
560 icvFSFlush(fs);
561 if( fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML )
562 icvPuts( fs, "</opencv_storage>\n" );
563 }
564
565 icvCloseFile(fs);
566 }
567
568 if( fs->outbuf && out )
569 {
570 out->resize(fs->outbuf->size());
571 std::copy(fs->outbuf->begin(), fs->outbuf->end(), out->begin());
572 }
573}

576/* closes file storage and deallocates buffers */
577CV_IMPL void
578cvReleaseFileStorage( CvFileStorage** p_fs )
579{
580 if( !p_fs )
581 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "NULL double pointer to file storage" );
582
583 if( *p_fs )
584 {
585 CvFileStorage* fs = *p_fs;
586 *p_fs = 0;
587
588 icvClose(fs, 0);
589
590 cvReleaseMemStorage( &fs->strstorage );
591 cvFree( &fs->buffer_start );
592 cvReleaseMemStorage( &fs->memstorage );
593
594 if( fs->outbuf )
595 delete fs->outbuf;
596
597 memset( fs, 0, sizeof(*fs) );
598 cvFree( &fs );
599 }
600}

603#define CV_HASHVAL_SCALE 33
604
605CV_IMPL CvStringHashNode*
606cvGetHashedKey( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* str, int len, int create_missing )
607{
608 CvStringHashNode* node = 0;
609 unsigned hashval = 0;
610 int i, tab_size;
611
612 if( !fs )
613 return 0;
614
615 CvStringHash* map = fs->str_hash;
616
617 if( len < 0 )
618 {
619 for( i = 0; str[i] != '\0'; i++ )
620 hashval = hashval*CV_HASHVAL_SCALE + (unsigned char)str[i];
621 len = i;
622 }
623 else for( i = 0; i < len; i++ )
624 hashval = hashval*CV_HASHVAL_SCALE + (unsigned char)str[i];
625
626 hashval &= INT_MAX;
627 tab_size = map->tab_size;
628 if( (tab_size & (tab_size - 1)) == 0 )
629 i = (int)(hashval & (tab_size - 1));
630 else
631 i = (int)(hashval % tab_size);
632
633 for( node = (CvStringHashNode*)(map->table[i]); node != 0; node = node->next )
634 {
635 if( node->hashval == hashval &&
636 node->str.len == len &&
637 memcmp( node->str.ptr, str, len ) == 0 )
638 break;
639 }
640
641 if( !node && create_missing )
642 {
643 node = (CvStringHashNode*)cvSetNew( (CvSet*)map );
644 node->hashval = hashval;
645 node->str = cvMemStorageAllocString( map->storage, str, len );
646 node->next = (CvStringHashNode*)(map->table[i]);
647 map->table[i] = node;
648 }
649
650 return node;
651}

653
654CV_IMPL CvFileNode*
655cvGetFileNode( CvFileStorage* fs, CvFileNode* _map_node,
656 const CvStringHashNode* key,
657 int create_missing )
658{
659 CvFileNode* value = 0;
660 int k = 0, attempts = 1;
661
662 if( !fs )
663 return 0;
664
665 CV_CHECK_FILE_STORAGE(fs);
666
667 if( !key )
668 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null key element" );
669
670 if( _map_node )
671 {
672 if( !fs->roots )
673 return 0;
674 attempts = fs->roots->total;
675 }
676
677 for( k = 0; k < attempts; k++ )
678 {
679 int i, tab_size;
680 CvFileNode* map_node = _map_node;
681 CvFileMapNode* another;
682 CvFileNodeHash* map;
683
684 if( !map_node )
685 map_node = (CvFileNode*)cvGetSeqElem( fs->roots, k );
686
687 if( !CV_NODE_IS_MAP(map_node->tag) )
688 {
689 if( (!CV_NODE_IS_SEQ(map_node->tag) || map_node->data.seq->total != 0) &&
690 CV_NODE_TYPE(map_node->tag) != CV_NODE_NONE )
691 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The node is neither a map nor an empty collection" );
692 return 0;
693 }
694
695 map = map_node->data.map;
696 tab_size = map->tab_size;
697
698 if( (tab_size & (tab_size - 1)) == 0 )
699 i = (int)(key->hashval & (tab_size - 1));
700 else
701 i = (int)(key->hashval % tab_size);
702
703 for( another = (CvFileMapNode*)(map->table[i]); another != 0; another = another->next )
704 if( another->key == key )
705 {
706 if( !create_missing )
707 {
708 value = &another->value;
709 return value;
710 }
711 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Duplicated key" );
712 }
713
714 if( k == attempts - 1 && create_missing )
715 {
716 CvFileMapNode* node = (CvFileMapNode*)cvSetNew( (CvSet*)map );
717 node->key = key;
718
719 node->next = (CvFileMapNode*)(map->table[i]);
720 map->table[i] = node;
721 value = (CvFileNode*)node;
722 }
723 }
724
725 return value;
726}

729CV_IMPL CvFileNode*
730cvGetFileNodeByName( const CvFileStorage* fs, const CvFileNode* _map_node, const char* str )
731{
732 CvFileNode* value = 0;
733 int i, len, tab_size;
734 unsigned hashval = 0;
735 int k = 0, attempts = 1;
736
737 if( !fs )
738 return 0;
739
740 CV_CHECK_FILE_STORAGE(fs);
741
742 if( !str )
743 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null element name" );
744
745 for( i = 0; str[i] != '\0'; i++ )
746 hashval = hashval*CV_HASHVAL_SCALE + (unsigned char)str[i];
747 hashval &= INT_MAX;
748 len = i;
749
750 if( !_map_node )
751 {
752 if( !fs->roots )
753 return 0;
754 attempts = fs->roots->total;
755 }
756
757 for( k = 0; k < attempts; k++ )
758 {
759 CvFileNodeHash* map;
760 const CvFileNode* map_node = _map_node;
761 CvFileMapNode* another;
762
763 if( !map_node )
764 map_node = (CvFileNode*)cvGetSeqElem( fs->roots, k );
765
766 if( !CV_NODE_IS_MAP(map_node->tag) )
767 {
768 if( (!CV_NODE_IS_SEQ(map_node->tag) || map_node->data.seq->total != 0) &&
769 CV_NODE_TYPE(map_node->tag) != CV_NODE_NONE )
770 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The node is neither a map nor an empty collection" );
771 return 0;
772 }
773
774 map = map_node->data.map;
775 tab_size = map->tab_size;
776
777 if( (tab_size & (tab_size - 1)) == 0 )
778 i = (int)(hashval & (tab_size - 1));
779 else
780 i = (int)(hashval % tab_size);
781
782 for( another = (CvFileMapNode*)(map->table[i]); another != 0; another = another->next )
783 {
784 const CvStringHashNode* key = another->key;
785
786 if( key->hashval == hashval &&
787 key->str.len == len &&
788 memcmp( key->str.ptr, str, len ) == 0 )
789 {
790 value = &another->value;
791 return value;
792 }
793 }
794 }
795
796 return value;
797}

846
847static char*
848icvDoubleToString( char* buf, double value )
849{
850 Cv64suf val;
851 unsigned ieee754_hi;
852
853 val.f = value;
854 ieee754_hi = (unsigned)(val.u >> 32);
855
856 if( (ieee754_hi & 0x7ff00000) != 0x7ff00000 )
857 {
858 int ivalue = cvRound(value);
859 if( ivalue == value )
860 sprintf( buf, "%d.", ivalue );
861 else
862 {
863 static const char* fmt = "%.16e";
864 char* ptr = buf;
865 sprintf( buf, fmt, value );
866 if( *ptr == '+' || *ptr == '-' )
867 ptr++;
868 for( ; cv_isdigit(*ptr); ptr++ )
869 ;
870 if( *ptr == ',' )
871 *ptr = '.';
872 }
873 }
874 else
875 {
876 unsigned ieee754_lo = (unsigned)val.u;
877 if( (ieee754_hi & 0x7fffffff) + (ieee754_lo != 0) > 0x7ff00000 )
878 strcpy( buf, ".Nan" );
879 else
880 strcpy( buf, (int)ieee754_hi < 0 ? "-.Inf" : ".Inf" );
881 }
882
883 return buf;
884}

886
887static char*
888icvFloatToString( char* buf, float value )
889{
890 Cv32suf val;
891 unsigned ieee754;
892 val.f = value;
893 ieee754 = val.u;
894
895 if( (ieee754 & 0x7f800000) != 0x7f800000 )
896 {
897 int ivalue = cvRound(value);
898 if( ivalue == value )
899 sprintf( buf, "%d.", ivalue );
900 else
901 {
902 static const char* fmt = "%.8e";
903 char* ptr = buf;
904 sprintf( buf, fmt, value );
905 if( *ptr == '+' || *ptr == '-' )
906 ptr++;
907 for( ; cv_isdigit(*ptr); ptr++ )
908 ;
909 if( *ptr == ',' )
910 *ptr = '.';
911 }
912 }
913 else
914 {
915 if( (ieee754 & 0x7fffffff) != 0x7f800000 )
916 strcpy( buf, ".Nan" );
917 else
918 strcpy( buf, (int)ieee754 < 0 ? "-.Inf" : ".Inf" );
919 }
920
921 return buf;
922}

924
925static void
926icvProcessSpecialDouble( CvFileStorage* fs, char* buf, double* value, char** endptr )
927{
928 char c = buf[0];
929 int inf_hi = 0x7ff00000;
930
931 if( c == '-' || c == '+' )
932 {
933 inf_hi = c == '-' ? 0xfff00000 : 0x7ff00000;
934 c = *++buf;
935 }
936
937 if( c != '.' )
938 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Bad format of floating-point constant" );
939
940 union{double d; uint64 i;} v;
941 v.d = 0.;
942 if( toupper(buf[1]) == 'I' && toupper(buf[2]) == 'N' && toupper(buf[3]) == 'F' )
943 v.i = (uint64)inf_hi << 32;
944 else if( toupper(buf[1]) == 'N' && toupper(buf[2]) == 'A' && toupper(buf[3]) == 'N' )
945 v.i = (uint64)-1;
946 else
947 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Bad format of floating-point constant" );
948 *value = v.d;
949
950 *endptr = buf + 4;
951}
952
953
954static double icv_strtod( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, char** endptr )
955{
956 double fval = strtod( ptr, endptr );
957 if( **endptr == '.' )
958 {
959 char* dot_pos = *endptr;
960 *dot_pos = ',';
961 double fval2 = strtod( ptr, endptr );
962 *dot_pos = '.';
963 if( *endptr > dot_pos )
964 fval = fval2;
965 else
966 *endptr = dot_pos;
967 }
968
969 if( *endptr == ptr || cv_isalpha(**endptr) )
970 icvProcessSpecialDouble( fs, ptr, &fval, endptr );
971
972 return fval;
973}

976/****************************************************************************************\
977* YAML Parser *
978\****************************************************************************************/
979
980static char*
981icvYMLSkipSpaces( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, int min_indent, int max_comment_indent )
982{
983 for(;;)
984 {
985 while( *ptr == ' ' )
986 ptr++;
987 if( *ptr == '#' )
988 {
989 if( ptr - fs->buffer_start > max_comment_indent )
990 return ptr;
991 *ptr = '\0';
992 }
993 else if( cv_isprint(*ptr) )
994 {
995 if( ptr - fs->buffer_start < min_indent )
996 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Incorrect indentation" );
997 break;
998 }
999 else if( *ptr == '\0' || *ptr == '\n' || *ptr == '\r' )
1000 {
1001 int max_size = (int)(fs->buffer_end - fs->buffer_start);
1002 ptr = icvGets( fs, fs->buffer_start, max_size );
1003 if( !ptr )
1004 {
1005 // emulate end of stream
1006 ptr = fs->buffer_start;
1007 ptr[0] = ptr[1] = ptr[2] = '.';
1008 ptr[3] = '\0';
1009 fs->dummy_eof = 1;
1010 break;
1011 }
1012 else
1013 {
1014 int l = (int)strlen(ptr);
1015 if( ptr[l-1] != '\n' && ptr[l-1] != '\r' && !icvEof(fs) )
1016 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Too long string or a last string w/o newline" );
1017 }
1018
1019 fs->lineno++;
1020 }
1021 else
1022 CV_PARSE_ERROR( *ptr == '\t' ? "Tabs are prohibited in YAML!" : "Invalid character" );
1023 }
1024
1025 return ptr;
1026}

1028
1029static char*
1030icvYMLParseKey( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr,
1031 CvFileNode* map_node, CvFileNode** value_placeholder )
1032{
1033 char c;
1034 char *endptr = ptr - 1, *saveptr;
1035 CvStringHashNode* str_hash_node;
1036
1037 if( *ptr == '-' )
1038 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Key may not start with \'-\'" );
1039
1040 do c = *++endptr;
1041 while( cv_isprint(c) && c != ':' );
1042
1043 if( c != ':' )
1044 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Missing \':\'" );
1045
1046 saveptr = endptr + 1;
1047 do c = *--endptr;
1048 while( c == ' ' );
1049
1050 ++endptr;
1051 if( endptr == ptr )
1052 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "An empty key" );
1053
1054 str_hash_node = cvGetHashedKey( fs, ptr, (int)(endptr - ptr), 1 );
1055 *value_placeholder = cvGetFileNode( fs, map_node, str_hash_node, 1 );
1056 ptr = saveptr;
1057
1058 return ptr;
1059}
1060
1061
1062static char*
1063icvYMLParseValue( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, CvFileNode* node,
1064 int parent_flags, int min_indent )
1065{
1066 char buf[CV_FS_MAX_LEN + 1024];
1067 char* endptr = 0;
1068 char c = ptr[0], d = ptr[1];
1069 int is_parent_flow = CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(parent_flags);
1070 int value_type = CV_NODE_NONE;
1071 int len;
1072
1073 memset( node, 0, sizeof(*node) );
1074
1075 if( c == '!' ) // handle explicit type specification
1076 {
1077 if( d == '!' || d == '^' )
1078 {
1079 ptr++;
1080 value_type |= CV_NODE_USER;
1081 }
1082
1083 endptr = ptr++;
1084 do d = *++endptr;
1085 while( cv_isprint(d) && d != ' ' );
1086 len = (int)(endptr - ptr);
1087 if( len == 0 )
1088 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Empty type name" );
1089 d = *endptr;
1090 *endptr = '\0';
1091
1092 if( len == 3 && !CV_NODE_IS_USER(value_type) )
1093 {
1094 if( memcmp( ptr, "str", 3 ) == 0 )
1095 value_type = CV_NODE_STRING;
1096 else if( memcmp( ptr, "int", 3 ) == 0 )
1097 value_type = CV_NODE_INT;
1098 else if( memcmp( ptr, "seq", 3 ) == 0 )
1099 value_type = CV_NODE_SEQ;
1100 else if( memcmp( ptr, "map", 3 ) == 0 )
1101 value_type = CV_NODE_MAP;
1102 }
1103 else if( len == 5 && !CV_NODE_IS_USER(value_type) )
1104 {
1105 if( memcmp( ptr, "float", 5 ) == 0 )
1106 value_type = CV_NODE_REAL;
1107 }
1108 else if( CV_NODE_IS_USER(value_type) )
1109 {
1110 node->info = cvFindType( ptr );
1111 if( !node->info )
1112 node->tag &= ~CV_NODE_USER;
1113 }
1114
1115 *endptr = d;
1116 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, endptr, min_indent, INT_MAX );
1117
1118 c = *ptr;
1119
1120 if( !CV_NODE_IS_USER(value_type) )
1121 {
1122 if( value_type == CV_NODE_STRING && c != '\'' && c != '\"' )
1123 goto force_string;
1124 if( value_type == CV_NODE_INT )
1125 goto force_int;
1126 if( value_type == CV_NODE_REAL )
1127 goto force_real;
1128 }
1129 }
1130
1131 if( cv_isdigit(c) ||
1132 ((c == '-' || c == '+') && (cv_isdigit(d) || d == '.')) ||
1133 (c == '.' && cv_isalnum(d))) // a number
1134 {
1135 double fval;
1136 int ival;
1137 endptr = ptr + (c == '-' || c == '+');
1138 while( cv_isdigit(*endptr) )
1139 endptr++;
1140 if( *endptr == '.' || *endptr == 'e' )
1141 {
1142force_real:
1143 fval = icv_strtod( fs, ptr, &endptr );
1144 /*if( endptr == ptr || cv_isalpha(*endptr) )
1145 icvProcessSpecialDouble( fs, endptr, &fval, &endptr ));*/
1146
1147 node->tag = CV_NODE_REAL;
1148 node->data.f = fval;
1149 }
1150 else
1151 {
1152force_int:
1153 ival = (int)strtol( ptr, &endptr, 0 );
1154 node->tag = CV_NODE_INT;
1155 node->data.i = ival;
1156 }
1157
1158 if( !endptr || endptr == ptr )
1159 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid numeric value (inconsistent explicit type specification?)" );
1160
1161 ptr = endptr;
1162 }
1163 else if( c == '\'' || c == '\"' ) // an explicit string
1164 {
1165 node->tag = CV_NODE_STRING;
1166 if( c == '\'' )
1167 for( len = 0; len < CV_FS_MAX_LEN; )
1168 {
1169 c = *++ptr;
1170 if( cv_isalnum(c) || (c != '\'' && cv_isprint(c)))
1171 buf[len++] = c;
1172 else if( c == '\'' )
1173 {
1174 c = *++ptr;
1175 if( c != '\'' )
1176 break;
1177 buf[len++] = c;
1178 }
1179 else
1180 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid character" );
1181 }
1182 else
1183 for( len = 0; len < CV_FS_MAX_LEN; )
1184 {
1185 c = *++ptr;
1186 if( cv_isalnum(c) || (c != '\\' && c != '\"' && cv_isprint(c)))
1187 buf[len++] = c;
1188 else if( c == '\"' )
1189 {
1190 ++ptr;
1191 break;
1192 }
1193 else if( c == '\\' )
1194 {
1195 d = *++ptr;
1196 if( d == '\'' )
1197 buf[len++] = d;
1198 else if( d == '\"' || d == '\\' || d == '\'' )
1199 buf[len++] = d;
1200 else if( d == 'n' )
1201 buf[len++] = '\n';
1202 else if( d == 'r' )
1203 buf[len++] = '\r';
1204 else if( d == 't' )
1205 buf[len++] = '\t';
1206 else if( d == 'x' || (cv_isdigit(d) && d < '8') )
1207 {
1208 int val, is_hex = d == 'x';
1209 c = ptr[3];
1210 ptr[3] = '\0';
1211 val = (int)strtol( ptr + is_hex, &endptr, is_hex ? 8 : 16 );
1212 ptr[3] = c;
1213 if( endptr == ptr + is_hex )
1214 buf[len++] = 'x';
1215 else
1216 {
1217 buf[len++] = (char)val;
1218 ptr = endptr;
1219 }
1220 }
1221 }
1222 else
1223 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid character" );
1224 }
1225
1226 if( len >= CV_FS_MAX_LEN )
1227 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Too long string literal" );
1228
1229 node->data.str = cvMemStorageAllocString( fs->memstorage, buf, len );
1230 }
1231 else if( c == '[' || c == '{' ) // collection as a flow
1232 {
1233 int new_min_indent = min_indent + !is_parent_flow;
1234 int struct_flags = CV_NODE_FLOW + (c == '{' ? CV_NODE_MAP : CV_NODE_SEQ);
1235 int is_simple = 1;
1236
1237 icvFSCreateCollection( fs, CV_NODE_TYPE(struct_flags) +
1238 (node->info ? CV_NODE_USER : 0), node );
1239
1240 d = c == '[' ? ']' : '}';
1241
1242 for( ++ptr ;;)
1243 {
1244 CvFileNode* elem = 0;
1245
1246 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, new_min_indent, INT_MAX );
1247 if( *ptr == '}' || *ptr == ']' )
1248 {
1249 if( *ptr != d )
1250 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "The wrong closing bracket" );
1251 ptr++;
1252 break;
1253 }
1254
1255 if( node->data.seq->total != 0 )
1256 {
1257 if( *ptr != ',' )
1258 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Missing , between the elements" );
1259 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr + 1, new_min_indent, INT_MAX );
1260 }
1261
1262 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) )
1263 {
1264 ptr = icvYMLParseKey( fs, ptr, node, &elem );
1265 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, new_min_indent, INT_MAX );
1266 }
1267 else
1268 {
1269 if( *ptr == ']' )
1270 break;
1271 elem = (CvFileNode*)cvSeqPush( node->data.seq, 0 );
1272 }
1273 ptr = icvYMLParseValue( fs, ptr, elem, struct_flags, new_min_indent );
1274 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) )
1275 elem->tag |= CV_NODE_NAMED;
1276 is_simple &= !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(elem->tag);
1277 }
1278 node->data.seq->flags |= is_simple ? CV_NODE_SEQ_SIMPLE : 0;
1279 }
1280 else
1281 {
1282 int indent, struct_flags, is_simple;
1283
1284 if( is_parent_flow || c != '-' )
1285 {
1286 // implicit (one-line) string or nested block-style collection
1287 if( !is_parent_flow )
1288 {
1289 if( c == '?' )
1290 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Complex keys are not supported" );
1291 if( c == '|' || c == '>' )
1292 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Multi-line text literals are not supported" );
1293 }
1294
1295force_string:
1296 endptr = ptr - 1;
1297
1298 do c = *++endptr;
1299 while( cv_isprint(c) &&
1300 (!is_parent_flow || (c != ',' && c != '}' && c != ']')) &&
1301 (is_parent_flow || c != ':' || value_type == CV_NODE_STRING));
1302
1303 if( endptr == ptr )
1304 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid character" );
1305
1306 if( is_parent_flow || c != ':' )
1307 {
1308 char* str_end = endptr;
1309 node->tag = CV_NODE_STRING;
1310 // strip spaces in the end of string
1311 do c = *--str_end;
1312 while( str_end > ptr && c == ' ' );
1313 str_end++;
1314 node->data.str = cvMemStorageAllocString( fs->memstorage, ptr, (int)(str_end - ptr) );
1315 ptr = endptr;
1316 return ptr;
1317 }
1318 struct_flags = CV_NODE_MAP;
1319 }
1320 else
1321 struct_flags = CV_NODE_SEQ;
1322
1323 icvFSCreateCollection( fs, struct_flags +
1324 (node->info ? CV_NODE_USER : 0), node );
1325
1326 indent = (int)(ptr - fs->buffer_start);
1327 is_simple = 1;
1328
1329 for(;;)
1330 {
1331 CvFileNode* elem = 0;
1332
1333 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) )
1334 {
1335 ptr = icvYMLParseKey( fs, ptr, node, &elem );
1336 }
1337 else
1338 {
1339 c = *ptr++;
1340 if( c != '-' )
1341 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Block sequence elements must be preceded with \'-\'" );
1342
1343 elem = (CvFileNode*)cvSeqPush( node->data.seq, 0 );
1344 }
1345
1346 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, indent + 1, INT_MAX );
1347 ptr = icvYMLParseValue( fs, ptr, elem, struct_flags, indent + 1 );
1348 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) )
1349 elem->tag |= CV_NODE_NAMED;
1350 is_simple &= !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(elem->tag);
1351
1352 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0, INT_MAX );
1353 if( ptr - fs->buffer_start != indent )
1354 {
1355 if( ptr - fs->buffer_start < indent )
1356 break;
1357 else
1358 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Incorrect indentation" );
1359 }
1360 if( memcmp( ptr, "...", 3 ) == 0 )
1361 break;
1362 }
1363
1364 node->data.seq->flags |= is_simple ? CV_NODE_SEQ_SIMPLE : 0;
1365 }
1366
1367 return ptr;
1368}
1369
1370
1371static void
1372icvYMLParse( CvFileStorage* fs )
1373{
1374 char* ptr = fs->buffer_start;
1375 int is_first = 1;
1376
1377 for(;;)
1378 {
1379 // 0. skip leading comments and directives and ...
1380 // 1. reach the first item
1381 for(;;)
1382 {
1383 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0, INT_MAX );
1384 if( !ptr )
1385 return;
1386
1387 if( *ptr == '%' )
1388 {
1389 if( memcmp( ptr, "%YAML:", 6 ) == 0 &&
1390 memcmp( ptr, "%YAML:1.", 8 ) != 0 )
1391 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Unsupported YAML version (it must be 1.x)" );
1392 *ptr = '\0';
1393 }
1394 else if( *ptr == '-' )
1395 {
1396 if( memcmp(ptr, "---", 3) == 0 )
1397 {
1398 ptr += 3;
1399 break;
1400 }
1401 else if( is_first )
1402 break;
1403 }
1404 else if( cv_isalnum(*ptr) || *ptr=='_')
1405 {
1406 if( !is_first )
1407 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "The YAML streams must start with '---', except the first one" );
1408 break;
1409 }
1410 else if( fs->dummy_eof )
1411 break;
1412 else
1413 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid or unsupported syntax" );
1414 }
1415
1416 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0, INT_MAX );
1417 if( memcmp( ptr, "...", 3 ) != 0 )
1418 {
1419 // 2. parse the collection
1420 CvFileNode* root_node = (CvFileNode*)cvSeqPush( fs->roots, 0 );
1421
1422 ptr = icvYMLParseValue( fs, ptr, root_node, CV_NODE_NONE, 0 );
1423 if( !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(root_node->tag) )
1424 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Only collections as YAML streams are supported by this parser" );
1425
1426 // 3. parse until the end of file or next collection
1427 ptr = icvYMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0, INT_MAX );
1428 if( !ptr )
1429 return;
1430 }
1431
1432 if( fs->dummy_eof )
1433 break;
1434 ptr += 3;
1435 is_first = 0;
1436 }
1437}

1439
1440/****************************************************************************************\
1441* YAML Emitter *
1442\****************************************************************************************/
1443
1444static void
1445icvYMLWrite( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key, const char* data )
1446{
1447 int i, keylen = 0;
1448 int datalen = 0;
1449 int struct_flags;
1450 char* ptr;
1451
1452 struct_flags = fs->struct_flags;
1453
1454 if( key && key[0] == '\0' )
1455 key = 0;
1456
1457 if( CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(struct_flags) )
1458 {
1459 if( (CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) ^ (key != 0)) )
1460 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "An attempt to add element without a key to a map, "
1461 "or add element with key to sequence" );
1462 }
1463 else
1464 {
1465 fs->is_first = 0;
1466 struct_flags = CV_NODE_EMPTY | (key ? CV_NODE_MAP : CV_NODE_SEQ);
1467 }
1468
1469 if( key )
1470 {
1471 keylen = (int)strlen(key);
1472 if( keylen == 0 )
1473 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "The key is an empty" );
1474
1475 if( keylen > CV_FS_MAX_LEN )
1476 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "The key is too long" );
1477 }
1478
1479 if( data )
1480 datalen = (int)strlen(data);
1481
1482 if( CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags) )
1483 {
1484 int new_offset;
1485 ptr = fs->buffer;
1486 if( !CV_NODE_IS_EMPTY(struct_flags) )
1487 *ptr++ = ',';
1488 new_offset = (int)(ptr - fs->buffer_start) + keylen + datalen;
1489 if( new_offset > fs->wrap_margin && new_offset - fs->struct_indent > 10 )
1490 {
1491 fs->buffer = ptr;
1492 ptr = icvFSFlush(fs);
1493 }
1494 else
1495 *ptr++ = ' ';
1496 }
1497 else
1498 {
1499 ptr = icvFSFlush(fs);
1500 if( !CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) )
1501 {
1502 *ptr++ = '-';
1503 if( data )
1504 *ptr++ = ' ';
1505 }
1506 }
1507
1508 if( key )
1509 {
1510 if( !cv_isalpha(key[0]) && key[0] != '_' )
1511 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Key must start with a letter or _" );
1512
1513 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, keylen );
1514
1515 for( i = 0; i < keylen; i++ )
1516 {
1517 char c = key[i];
1518
1519 ptr[i] = c;
1520 if( !cv_isalnum(c) && c != '-' && c != '_' && c != ' ' )
1521 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Key names may only contain alphanumeric characters [a-zA-Z0-9], '-', '_' and ' '" );
1522 }
1523
1524 ptr += keylen;
1525 *ptr++ = ':';
1526 if( !CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags) && data )
1527 *ptr++ = ' ';
1528 }
1529
1530 if( data )
1531 {
1532 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, datalen );
1533 memcpy( ptr, data, datalen );
1534 ptr += datalen;
1535 }
1536
1537 fs->buffer = ptr;
1538 fs->struct_flags = struct_flags & ~CV_NODE_EMPTY;
1539}

1541
1542static void
1543icvYMLStartWriteStruct( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key, int struct_flags,
1544 const char* type_name CV_DEFAULT(0))
1545{
1546 int parent_flags;
1547 char buf[CV_FS_MAX_LEN + 1024];
1548 const char* data = 0;
1549
1550 struct_flags = (struct_flags & (CV_NODE_TYPE_MASK|CV_NODE_FLOW)) | CV_NODE_EMPTY;
1551 if( !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(struct_flags))
1552 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg,
1553 "Some collection type - CV_NODE_SEQ or CV_NODE_MAP, must be specified" );
1554
1555 if( CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags) )
1556 {
1557 char c = CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) ? '{' : '[';
1558 struct_flags |= CV_NODE_FLOW;
1559
1560 if( type_name )
1561 sprintf( buf, "!!%s %c", type_name, c );
1562 else
1563 {
1564 buf[0] = c;
1565 buf[1] = '\0';
1566 }
1567 data = buf;
1568 }
1569 else if( type_name )
1570 {
1571 sprintf( buf, "!!%s", type_name );
1572 data = buf;
1573 }
1574
1575 icvYMLWrite( fs, key, data );
1576
1577 parent_flags = fs->struct_flags;
1578 cvSeqPush( fs->write_stack, &parent_flags );
1579 fs->struct_flags = struct_flags;
1580
1581 if( !CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(parent_flags) )
1582 fs->struct_indent += CV_YML_INDENT + CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags);
1583}

1585
1586static void
1587icvYMLEndWriteStruct( CvFileStorage* fs )
1588{
1589 int parent_flags = 0, struct_flags;
1590 char* ptr;
1591
1592 struct_flags = fs->struct_flags;
1593 if( fs->write_stack->total == 0 )
1594 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "EndWriteStruct w/o matching StartWriteStruct" );
1595
1596 cvSeqPop( fs->write_stack, &parent_flags );
1597
1598 if( CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags) )
1599 {
1600 ptr = fs->buffer;
1601 if( ptr > fs->buffer_start + fs->struct_indent && !CV_NODE_IS_EMPTY(struct_flags) )
1602 *ptr++ = ' ';
1603 *ptr++ = CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) ? '}' : ']';
1604 fs->buffer = ptr;
1605 }
1606 else if( CV_NODE_IS_EMPTY(struct_flags) )
1607 {
1608 ptr = icvFSFlush(fs);
1609 memcpy( ptr, CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) ? "{}" : "[]", 2 );
1610 fs->buffer = ptr + 2;
1611 }
1612
1613 if( !CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(parent_flags) )
1614 fs->struct_indent -= CV_YML_INDENT + CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags);
1615 assert( fs->struct_indent >= 0 );
1616
1617 fs->struct_flags = parent_flags;
1618}

1621static void
1622icvYMLStartNextStream( CvFileStorage* fs )
1623{
1624 if( !fs->is_first )
1625 {
1626 while( fs->write_stack->total > 0 )
1627 icvYMLEndWriteStruct(fs);
1628
1629 fs->struct_indent = 0;
1630 icvFSFlush(fs);
1631 icvPuts( fs, "...\n" );
1632 icvPuts( fs, "---\n" );
1633 fs->buffer = fs->buffer_start;
1634 }
1635}

1653
1654static void
1655icvYMLWriteString( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key,
1656 const char* str, int quote CV_DEFAULT(0))
1657{
1658 char buf[CV_FS_MAX_LEN*4+16];
1659 char* data = (char*)str;
1660 int i, len;
1661
1662 if( !str )
1663 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null string pointer" );
1664
1665 len = (int)strlen(str);
1666 if( len > CV_FS_MAX_LEN )
1667 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "The written string is too long" );
1668
1669 if( quote || len == 0 || str[0] != str[len-1] || (str[0] != '\"' && str[0] != '\'') )
1670 {
1671 int need_quote = quote || len == 0;
1672 data = buf;
1673 *data++ = '\"';
1674 for( i = 0; i < len; i++ )
1675 {
1676 char c = str[i];
1677
1678 if( !need_quote && !cv_isalnum(c) && c != '_' && c != ' ' && c != '-' &&
1679 c != '(' && c != ')' && c != '/' && c != '+' && c != ';' )
1680 need_quote = 1;
1681
1682 if( !cv_isalnum(c) && (!cv_isprint(c) || c == '\\' || c == '\'' || c == '\"') )
1683 {
1684 *data++ = '\\';
1685 if( cv_isprint(c) )
1686 *data++ = c;
1687 else if( c == '\n' )
1688 *data++ = 'n';
1689 else if( c == '\r' )
1690 *data++ = 'r';
1691 else if( c == '\t' )
1692 *data++ = 't';
1693 else
1694 {
1695 sprintf( data, "x%02x", c );
1696 data += 3;
1697 }
1698 }
1699 else
1700 *data++ = c;
1701 }
1702 if( !need_quote && (cv_isdigit(str[0]) ||
1703 str[0] == '+' || str[0] == '-' || str[0] == '.' ))
1704 need_quote = 1;
1705
1706 if( need_quote )
1707 *data++ = '\"';
1708 *data++ = '\0';
1709 data = buf + !need_quote;
1710 }
1711
1712 icvYMLWrite( fs, key, data );
1713}

1715
1716static void
1717icvYMLWriteComment( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* comment, int eol_comment )
1718{
1719 int len; //, indent;
1720 int multiline;
1721 const char* eol;
1722 char* ptr;
1723
1724 if( !comment )
1725 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null comment" );
1726
1727 len = (int)strlen(comment);
1728 eol = strchr(comment, '\n');
1729 multiline = eol != 0;
1730 ptr = fs->buffer;
1731
1732 if( !eol_comment || multiline ||
1733 fs->buffer_end - ptr < len || ptr == fs->buffer_start )
1734 ptr = icvFSFlush( fs );
1735 else
1736 *ptr++ = ' ';
1737
1738 while( comment )
1739 {
1740 *ptr++ = '#';
1741 *ptr++ = ' ';
1742 if( eol )
1743 {
1744 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, (int)(eol - comment) + 1 );
1745 memcpy( ptr, comment, eol - comment + 1 );
1746 fs->buffer = ptr + (eol - comment);
1747 comment = eol + 1;
1748 eol = strchr( comment, '\n' );
1749 }
1750 else
1751 {
1752 len = (int)strlen(comment);
1753 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, len );
1754 memcpy( ptr, comment, len );
1755 fs->buffer = ptr + len;
1756 comment = 0;
1757 }
1758 ptr = icvFSFlush( fs );
1759 }
1760}

1762
1763/****************************************************************************************\
1764* XML Parser *
1765\****************************************************************************************/
1766
1767#define CV_XML_INSIDE_COMMENT 1
1768#define CV_XML_INSIDE_TAG 2
1769#define CV_XML_INSIDE_DIRECTIVE 3
1770
1771static char*
1772icvXMLSkipSpaces( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, int mode )
1773{
1774 int level = 0;
1775
1776 for(;;)
1777 {
1778 char c;
1779 ptr--;
1780
1781 if( mode == CV_XML_INSIDE_COMMENT )
1782 {
1783 do c = *++ptr;
1784 while( cv_isprint_or_tab(c) && (c != '-' || ptr[1] != '-' || ptr[2] != '>') );
1785
1786 if( c == '-' )
1787 {
1788 assert( ptr[1] == '-' && ptr[2] == '>' );
1789 mode = 0;
1790 ptr += 3;
1791 }
1792 }
1793 else if( mode == CV_XML_INSIDE_DIRECTIVE )
1794 {
1795 // !!!NOTE!!! This is not quite correct, but should work in most cases
1796 do
1797 {
1798 c = *++ptr;
1799 level += c == '<';
1800 level -= c == '>';
1801 if( level < 0 )
1802 return ptr;
1803 } while( cv_isprint_or_tab(c) );
1804 }
1805 else
1806 {
1807 do c = *++ptr;
1808 while( c == ' ' || c == '\t' );
1809
1810 if( c == '<' && ptr[1] == '!' && ptr[2] == '-' && ptr[3] == '-' )
1811 {
1812 if( mode != 0 )
1813 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Comments are not allowed here" );
1814 mode = CV_XML_INSIDE_COMMENT;
1815 ptr += 4;
1816 }
1817 else if( cv_isprint(c) )
1818 break;
1819 }
1820
1821 if( !cv_isprint(*ptr) )
1822 {
1823 int max_size = (int)(fs->buffer_end - fs->buffer_start);
1824 if( *ptr != '\0' && *ptr != '\n' && *ptr != '\r' )
1825 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid character in the stream" );
1826 ptr = icvGets( fs, fs->buffer_start, max_size );
1827 if( !ptr )
1828 {
1829 ptr = fs->buffer_start;
1830 *ptr = '\0';
1831 fs->dummy_eof = 1;
1832 break;
1833 }
1834 else
1835 {
1836 int l = (int)strlen(ptr);
1837 if( ptr[l-1] != '\n' && ptr[l-1] != '\r' && !icvEof(fs) )
1838 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Too long string or a last string w/o newline" );
1839 }
1840 fs->lineno++;
1841 }
1842 }
1843 return ptr;
1844}

1846
1847static char*
1848icvXMLParseTag( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, CvStringHashNode** _tag,
1849 CvAttrList** _list, int* _tag_type );
1850
1851static char*
1852icvXMLParseValue( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, CvFileNode* node,
1853 int value_type CV_DEFAULT(CV_NODE_NONE))
1854{
1855 CvFileNode *elem = node;
1856 int have_space = 1, is_simple = 1;
1857 int is_user_type = CV_NODE_IS_USER(value_type);
1858 memset( node, 0, sizeof(*node) );
1859
1860 value_type = CV_NODE_TYPE(value_type);
1861
1862 for(;;)
1863 {
1864 char c = *ptr, d;
1865 char* endptr;
1866
1867 if( cv_isspace(c) || c == '\0' || (c == '<' && ptr[1] == '!' && ptr[2] == '-') )
1868 {
1869 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0 );
1870 have_space = 1;
1871 c = *ptr;
1872 }
1873
1874 d = ptr[1];
1875
1876 if( c =='<' || c == '\0' )
1877 {
1878 CvStringHashNode *key = 0, *key2 = 0;
1879 CvAttrList* list = 0;
1880 CvTypeInfo* info = 0;
1881 int tag_type = 0;
1882 int is_noname = 0;
1883 const char* type_name = 0;
1884 int elem_type = CV_NODE_NONE;
1885
1886 if( d == '/' || c == '\0' )
1887 break;
1888
1889 ptr = icvXMLParseTag( fs, ptr, &key, &list, &tag_type );
1890
1891 if( tag_type == CV_XML_DIRECTIVE_TAG )
1892 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Directive tags are not allowed here" );
1893 if( tag_type == CV_XML_EMPTY_TAG )
1894 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Empty tags are not supported" );
1895
1896 assert( tag_type == CV_XML_OPENING_TAG );
1897
1898 type_name = list ? cvAttrValue( list, "type_id" ) : 0;
1899 if( type_name )
1900 {
1901 if( strcmp( type_name, "str" ) == 0 )
1902 elem_type = CV_NODE_STRING;
1903 else if( strcmp( type_name, "map" ) == 0 )
1904 elem_type = CV_NODE_MAP;
1905 else if( strcmp( type_name, "seq" ) == 0 )
1906 elem_type = CV_NODE_SEQ;
1907 else
1908 {
1909 info = cvFindType( type_name );
1910 if( info )
1911 elem_type = CV_NODE_USER;
1912 }
1913 }
1914
1915 is_noname = key->str.len == 1 && key->str.ptr[0] == '_';
1916 if( !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(node->tag) )
1917 {
1918 icvFSCreateCollection( fs, is_noname ? CV_NODE_SEQ : CV_NODE_MAP, node );
1919 }
1920 else if( is_noname ^ CV_NODE_IS_SEQ(node->tag) )
1921 CV_PARSE_ERROR( is_noname ? "Map element should have a name" :
1922 "Sequence element should not have name (use <_></_>)" );
1923
1924 if( is_noname )
1925 elem = (CvFileNode*)cvSeqPush( node->data.seq, 0 );
1926 else
1927 elem = cvGetFileNode( fs, node, key, 1 );
1928
1929 ptr = icvXMLParseValue( fs, ptr, elem, elem_type);
1930 if( !is_noname )
1931 elem->tag |= CV_NODE_NAMED;
1932 is_simple &= !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(elem->tag);
1933 elem->info = info;
1934 ptr = icvXMLParseTag( fs, ptr, &key2, &list, &tag_type );
1935 if( tag_type != CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG || key2 != key )
1936 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Mismatched closing tag" );
1937 have_space = 1;
1938 }
1939 else
1940 {
1941 if( !have_space )
1942 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "There should be space between literals" );
1943
1944 elem = node;
1945 if( node->tag != CV_NODE_NONE )
1946 {
1947 if( !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(node->tag) )
1948 icvFSCreateCollection( fs, CV_NODE_SEQ, node );
1949
1950 elem = (CvFileNode*)cvSeqPush( node->data.seq, 0 );
1951 elem->info = 0;
1952 }
1953
1954 if( value_type != CV_NODE_STRING &&
1955 (cv_isdigit(c) || ((c == '-' || c == '+') &&
1956 (cv_isdigit(d) || d == '.')) || (c == '.' && cv_isalnum(d))) ) // a number
1957 {
1958 double fval;
1959 int ival;
1960 endptr = ptr + (c == '-' || c == '+');
1961 while( cv_isdigit(*endptr) )
1962 endptr++;
1963 if( *endptr == '.' || *endptr == 'e' )
1964 {
1965 fval = icv_strtod( fs, ptr, &endptr );
1966 /*if( endptr == ptr || cv_isalpha(*endptr) )
1967 icvProcessSpecialDouble( fs, ptr, &fval, &endptr ));*/
1968 elem->tag = CV_NODE_REAL;
1969 elem->data.f = fval;
1970 }
1971 else
1972 {
1973 ival = (int)strtol( ptr, &endptr, 0 );
1974 elem->tag = CV_NODE_INT;
1975 elem->data.i = ival;
1976 }
1977
1978 if( endptr == ptr )
1979 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid numeric value (inconsistent explicit type specification?)" );
1980
1981 ptr = endptr;
1982 }
1983 else
1984 {
1985 // string
1986 char buf[CV_FS_MAX_LEN+16];
1987 int i = 0, len, is_quoted = 0;
1988 elem->tag = CV_NODE_STRING;
1989 if( c == '\"' )
1990 is_quoted = 1;
1991 else
1992 --ptr;
1993
1994 for( ;; )
1995 {
1996 c = *++ptr;
1997 if( !cv_isalnum(c) )
1998 {
1999 if( c == '\"' )
2000 {
2001 if( !is_quoted )
2002 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Literal \" is not allowed within a string. Use &quot;" );
2003 ++ptr;
2004 break;
2005 }
2006 else if( !cv_isprint(c) || c == '<' || (!is_quoted && cv_isspace(c)))
2007 {
2008 if( is_quoted )
2009 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Closing \" is expected" );
2010 break;
2011 }
2012 else if( c == '\'' || c == '>' )
2013 {
2014 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Literal \' or > are not allowed. Use &apos; or &gt;" );
2015 }
2016 else if( c == '&' )
2017 {
2018 if( *++ptr == '#' )
2019 {
2020 int val, base = 10;
2021 ptr++;
2022 if( *ptr == 'x' )
2023 {
2024 base = 16;
2025 ptr++;
2026 }
2027 val = (int)strtol( ptr, &endptr, base );
2028 if( (unsigned)val > (unsigned)255 ||
2029 !endptr || *endptr != ';' )
2030 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid numeric value in the string" );
2031 c = (char)val;
2032 }
2033 else
2034 {
2035 endptr = ptr;
2036 do c = *++endptr;
2037 while( cv_isalnum(c) );
2038 if( c != ';' )
2039 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid character in the symbol entity name" );
2040 len = (int)(endptr - ptr);
2041 if( len == 2 && memcmp( ptr, "lt", len ) == 0 )
2042 c = '<';
2043 else if( len == 2 && memcmp( ptr, "gt", len ) == 0 )
2044 c = '>';
2045 else if( len == 3 && memcmp( ptr, "amp", len ) == 0 )
2046 c = '&';
2047 else if( len == 4 && memcmp( ptr, "apos", len ) == 0 )
2048 c = '\'';
2049 else if( len == 4 && memcmp( ptr, "quot", len ) == 0 )
2050 c = '\"';
2051 else
2052 {
2053 memcpy( buf + i, ptr-1, len + 2 );
2054 i += len + 2;
2055 }
2056 }
2057 ptr = endptr;
2058 }
2059 }
2060 buf[i++] = c;
2061 if( i >= CV_FS_MAX_LEN )
2062 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Too long string literal" );
2063 }
2064 elem->data.str = cvMemStorageAllocString( fs->memstorage, buf, i );
2065 }
2066
2067 if( !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(value_type) && value_type != CV_NODE_NONE )
2068 break;
2069 have_space = 0;
2070 }
2071 }
2072
2073 if( (CV_NODE_TYPE(node->tag) == CV_NODE_NONE ||
2074 (CV_NODE_TYPE(node->tag) != value_type &&
2075 !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(node->tag))) &&
2076 CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(value_type) )
2077 {
2078 icvFSCreateCollection( fs, CV_NODE_IS_MAP(value_type) ?
2079 CV_NODE_MAP : CV_NODE_SEQ, node );
2080 }
2081
2082 if( value_type != CV_NODE_NONE &&
2083 value_type != CV_NODE_TYPE(node->tag) )
2084 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "The actual type is different from the specified type" );
2085
2086 if( CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(node->tag) && is_simple )
2087 node->data.seq->flags |= CV_NODE_SEQ_SIMPLE;
2088
2089 node->tag |= is_user_type ? CV_NODE_USER : 0;
2090 return ptr;
2091}
2092
2093
2094static char*
2095icvXMLParseTag( CvFileStorage* fs, char* ptr, CvStringHashNode** _tag,
2096 CvAttrList** _list, int* _tag_type )
2097{
2098 int tag_type = 0;
2099 CvStringHashNode* tagname = 0;
2100 CvAttrList *first = 0, *last = 0;
2101 int count = 0, max_count = 4;
2102 int attr_buf_size = (max_count*2 + 1)*sizeof(char*) + sizeof(CvAttrList);
2103 char* endptr;
2104 char c;
2105 int have_space;
2106
2107 if( *ptr == '\0' )
2108 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Preliminary end of the stream" );
2109
2110 if( *ptr != '<' )
2111 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Tag should start with \'<\'" );
2112
2113 ptr++;
2114 if( cv_isalnum(*ptr) || *ptr == '_' )
2115 tag_type = CV_XML_OPENING_TAG;
2116 else if( *ptr == '/' )
2117 {
2118 tag_type = CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG;
2119 ptr++;
2120 }
2121 else if( *ptr == '?' )
2122 {
2123 tag_type = CV_XML_HEADER_TAG;
2124 ptr++;
2125 }
2126 else if( *ptr == '!' )
2127 {
2128 tag_type = CV_XML_DIRECTIVE_TAG;
2129 assert( ptr[1] != '-' || ptr[2] != '-' );
2130 ptr++;
2131 }
2132 else
2133 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Unknown tag type" );
2134
2135 for(;;)
2136 {
2137 CvStringHashNode* attrname;
2138
2139 if( !cv_isalpha(*ptr) && *ptr != '_' )
2140 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Name should start with a letter or underscore" );
2141
2142 endptr = ptr - 1;
2143 do c = *++endptr;
2144 while( cv_isalnum(c) || c == '_' || c == '-' );
2145
2146 attrname = cvGetHashedKey( fs, ptr, (int)(endptr - ptr), 1 );
2147 ptr = endptr;
2148
2149 if( !tagname )
2150 tagname = attrname;
2151 else
2152 {
2153 if( tag_type == CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG )
2154 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Closing tag should not contain any attributes" );
2155
2156 if( !last || count >= max_count )
2157 {
2158 CvAttrList* chunk;
2159
2160 chunk = (CvAttrList*)cvMemStorageAlloc( fs->memstorage, attr_buf_size );
2161 memset( chunk, 0, attr_buf_size );
2162 chunk->attr = (const char**)(chunk + 1);
2163 count = 0;
2164 if( !last )
2165 first = last = chunk;
2166 else
2167 last = last->next = chunk;
2168 }
2169 last->attr[count*2] = attrname->str.ptr;
2170 }
2171
2172 if( last )
2173 {
2174 CvFileNode stub;
2175
2176 if( *ptr != '=' )
2177 {
2178 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, CV_XML_INSIDE_TAG );
2179 if( *ptr != '=' )
2180 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Attribute name should be followed by \'=\'" );
2181 }
2182
2183 c = *++ptr;
2184 if( c != '\"' && c != '\'' )
2185 {
2186 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, CV_XML_INSIDE_TAG );
2187 if( *ptr != '\"' && *ptr != '\'' )
2188 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Attribute value should be put into single or double quotes" );
2189 }
2190
2191 ptr = icvXMLParseValue( fs, ptr, &stub, CV_NODE_STRING );
2192 assert( stub.tag == CV_NODE_STRING );
2193 last->attr[count*2+1] = stub.data.str.ptr;
2194 count++;
2195 }
2196
2197 c = *ptr;
2198 have_space = cv_isspace(c) || c == '\0';
2199
2200 if( c != '>' )
2201 {
2202 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, CV_XML_INSIDE_TAG );
2203 c = *ptr;
2204 }
2205
2206 if( c == '>' )
2207 {
2208 if( tag_type == CV_XML_HEADER_TAG )
2209 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid closing tag for <?xml ..." );
2210 ptr++;
2211 break;
2212 }
2213 else if( c == '?' && tag_type == CV_XML_HEADER_TAG )
2214 {
2215 if( ptr[1] != '>' )
2216 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Invalid closing tag for <?xml ..." );
2217 ptr += 2;
2218 break;
2219 }
2220 else if( c == '/' && ptr[1] == '>' && tag_type == CV_XML_OPENING_TAG )
2221 {
2222 tag_type = CV_XML_EMPTY_TAG;
2223 ptr += 2;
2224 break;
2225 }
2226
2227 if( !have_space )
2228 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "There should be space between attributes" );
2229 }
2230
2231 *_tag = tagname;
2232 *_tag_type = tag_type;
2233 *_list = first;
2234
2235 return ptr;
2236}

2238
2239static void
2240icvXMLParse( CvFileStorage* fs )
2241{
2242 char* ptr = fs->buffer_start;
2243 CvStringHashNode *key = 0, *key2 = 0;
2244 CvAttrList* list = 0;
2245 int tag_type = 0;
2246
2247 // CV_XML_INSIDE_TAG is used to prohibit leading comments
2248 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, CV_XML_INSIDE_TAG );
2249
2250 if( memcmp( ptr, "<?xml", 5 ) != 0 )
2251
2252 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Valid XML should start with \'<?xml ...?>\'" );
2253
2254 ptr = icvXMLParseTag( fs, ptr, &key, &list, &tag_type );
2255
2256 /*{
2257 const char* version = cvAttrValue( list, "version" );
2258 if( version && strncmp( version, "1.", 2 ) != 0 )
2259 CV_Error( CV_StsParseError, "Unsupported version of XML" );
2260 }*/
2261 // we support any 8-bit encoding, so we do not need to check the actual encoding.
2262 // we do not support utf-16, but in the case of utf-16 we will not get here anyway.
2263 /*{
2264 const char* encoding = cvAttrValue( list, "encoding" );
2265 if( encoding && strcmp( encoding, "ASCII" ) != 0 &&
2266 strcmp( encoding, "UTF-8" ) != 0 &&
2267 strcmp( encoding, "utf-8" ) != 0 )
2268 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "Unsupported encoding" );
2269 }*/
2270
2271 while( *ptr != '\0' )
2272 {
2273 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0 );
2274
2275 if( *ptr != '\0' )
2276 {
2277 CvFileNode* root_node;
2278 ptr = icvXMLParseTag( fs, ptr, &key, &list, &tag_type );
2279 if( tag_type != CV_XML_OPENING_TAG ||
2280 strcmp(key->str.ptr,"opencv_storage") != 0 )
2281 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "<opencv_storage> tag is missing" );
2282
2283 root_node = (CvFileNode*)cvSeqPush( fs->roots, 0 );
2284 ptr = icvXMLParseValue( fs, ptr, root_node, CV_NODE_NONE );
2285 ptr = icvXMLParseTag( fs, ptr, &key2, &list, &tag_type );
2286 if( tag_type != CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG || key != key2 )
2287 CV_PARSE_ERROR( "</opencv_storage> tag is missing" );
2288 ptr = icvXMLSkipSpaces( fs, ptr, 0 );
2289 }
2290 }
2291
2292 assert( fs->dummy_eof != 0 );
2293}

2296/****************************************************************************************\
2297* XML Emitter *
2298\****************************************************************************************/
2299
2300#define icvXMLFlush icvFSFlush
2301
2302static void
2303icvXMLWriteTag( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key, int tag_type, CvAttrList list )
2304{
2305 char* ptr = fs->buffer;
2306 int i, len = 0;
2307 int struct_flags = fs->struct_flags;
2308
2309 if( key && key[0] == '\0' )
2310 key = 0;
2311
2312 if( tag_type == CV_XML_OPENING_TAG || tag_type == CV_XML_EMPTY_TAG )
2313 {
2314 if( CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(struct_flags) )
2315 {
2316 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(struct_flags) ^ (key != 0) )
2317 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "An attempt to add element without a key to a map, "
2318 "or add element with key to sequence" );
2319 }
2320 else
2321 {
2322 struct_flags = CV_NODE_EMPTY + (key ? CV_NODE_MAP : CV_NODE_SEQ);
2323 fs->is_first = 0;
2324 }
2325
2326 if( !CV_NODE_IS_EMPTY(struct_flags) )
2327 ptr = icvXMLFlush(fs);
2328 }
2329
2330 if( !key )
2331 key = "_";
2332 else if( key[0] == '_' && key[1] == '\0' )
2333 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "A single _ is a reserved tag name" );
2334
2335 len = (int)strlen( key );
2336 *ptr++ = '<';
2337 if( tag_type == CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG )
2338 {
2339 if( list.attr )
2340 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Closing tag should not include any attributes" );
2341 *ptr++ = '/';
2342 }
2343
2344 if( !cv_isalpha(key[0]) && key[0] != '_' )
2345 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Key should start with a letter or _" );
2346
2347 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, len );
2348 for( i = 0; i < len; i++ )
2349 {
2350 char c = key[i];
2351 if( !cv_isalnum(c) && c != '_' && c != '-' )
2352 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Key name may only contain alphanumeric characters [a-zA-Z0-9], '-' and '_'" );
2353 ptr[i] = c;
2354 }
2355 ptr += len;
2356
2357 for(;;)
2358 {
2359 const char** attr = list.attr;
2360
2361 for( ; attr && attr[0] != 0; attr += 2 )
2362 {
2363 int len0 = (int)strlen(attr[0]);
2364 int len1 = (int)strlen(attr[1]);
2365
2366 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, len0 + len1 + 4 );
2367 *ptr++ = ' ';
2368 memcpy( ptr, attr[0], len0 );
2369 ptr += len0;
2370 *ptr++ = '=';
2371 *ptr++ = '\"';
2372 memcpy( ptr, attr[1], len1 );
2373 ptr += len1;
2374 *ptr++ = '\"';
2375 }
2376 if( !list.next )
2377 break;
2378 list = *list.next;
2379 }
2380
2381 if( tag_type == CV_XML_EMPTY_TAG )
2382 *ptr++ = '/';
2383 *ptr++ = '>';
2384 fs->buffer = ptr;
2385 fs->struct_flags = struct_flags & ~CV_NODE_EMPTY;
2386}

2388
2389static void
2390icvXMLStartWriteStruct( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key, int struct_flags,
2391 const char* type_name CV_DEFAULT(0))
2392{
2393 CvXMLStackRecord parent;
2394 const char* attr[10];
2395 int idx = 0;
2396
2397 struct_flags = (struct_flags & (CV_NODE_TYPE_MASK|CV_NODE_FLOW)) | CV_NODE_EMPTY;
2398 if( !CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(struct_flags))
2399 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg,
2400 "Some collection type: CV_NODE_SEQ or CV_NODE_MAP must be specified" );
2401
2402 if( type_name )
2403 {
2404 attr[idx++] = "type_id";
2405 attr[idx++] = type_name;
2406 }
2407 attr[idx++] = 0;
2408
2409 icvXMLWriteTag( fs, key, CV_XML_OPENING_TAG, cvAttrList(attr,0) );
2410
2411 parent.struct_flags = fs->struct_flags & ~CV_NODE_EMPTY;
2412 parent.struct_indent = fs->struct_indent;
2413 parent.struct_tag = fs->struct_tag;
2414 cvSaveMemStoragePos( fs->strstorage, &parent.pos );
2415 cvSeqPush( fs->write_stack, &parent );
2416
2417 fs->struct_indent += CV_XML_INDENT;
2418 if( !CV_NODE_IS_FLOW(struct_flags) )
2419 icvXMLFlush( fs );
2420
2421 fs->struct_flags = struct_flags;
2422 if( key )
2423 {
2424 fs->struct_tag = cvMemStorageAllocString( fs->strstorage, (char*)key, -1 );
2425 }
2426 else
2427 {
2428 fs->struct_tag.ptr = 0;
2429 fs->struct_tag.len = 0;
2430 }
2431}

2434static void
2435icvXMLEndWriteStruct( CvFileStorage* fs )
2436{
2437 CvXMLStackRecord parent;
2438
2439 if( fs->write_stack->total == 0 )
2440 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "An extra closing tag" );
2441
2442 icvXMLWriteTag( fs, fs->struct_tag.ptr, CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG, cvAttrList(0,0) );
2443 cvSeqPop( fs->write_stack, &parent );
2444
2445 fs->struct_indent = parent.struct_indent;
2446 fs->struct_flags = parent.struct_flags;
2447 fs->struct_tag = parent.struct_tag;
2448 cvRestoreMemStoragePos( fs->strstorage, &parent.pos );
2449}

2452static void
2453icvXMLStartNextStream( CvFileStorage* fs )
2454{
2455 if( !fs->is_first )
2456 {
2457 while( fs->write_stack->total > 0 )
2458 icvXMLEndWriteStruct(fs);
2459
2460 fs->struct_indent = 0;
2461 icvXMLFlush(fs);
2462 /* XML does not allow multiple top-level elements,
2463 so we just put a comment and continue
2464 the current (and the only) "stream" */
2465 icvPuts( fs, "\n<!-- next stream -->\n" );
2466 /*fputs( "</opencv_storage>\n", fs->file );
2467 fputs( "<opencv_storage>\n", fs->file );*/
2468 fs->buffer = fs->buffer_start;

2473static void
2474icvXMLWriteScalar( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key, const char* data, int len )
2475{
2476 if( CV_NODE_IS_MAP(fs->struct_flags) ||
2477 (!CV_NODE_IS_COLLECTION(fs->struct_flags) && key) )
2478 {
2479 icvXMLWriteTag( fs, key, CV_XML_OPENING_TAG, cvAttrList(0,0) );
2480 char* ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, fs->buffer, len );
2481 memcpy( ptr, data, len );
2482 fs->buffer = ptr + len;
2483 icvXMLWriteTag( fs, key, CV_XML_CLOSING_TAG, cvAttrList(0,0) );
2484 }
2485 else
2486 {
2487 char* ptr = fs->buffer;
2488 int new_offset = (int)(ptr - fs->buffer_start) + len;
2489
2490 if( key )
2491 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "elements with keys can not be written to sequence" );
2492
2493 fs->struct_flags = CV_NODE_SEQ;
2494
2495 if( (new_offset > fs->wrap_margin && new_offset - fs->struct_indent > 10) ||
2496 (ptr > fs->buffer_start && ptr[-1] == '>' && !CV_NODE_IS_EMPTY(fs->struct_flags)) )
2497 {
2498 ptr = icvXMLFlush(fs);
2499 }
2500 else if( ptr > fs->buffer_start + fs->struct_indent && ptr[-1] != '>' )
2501 *ptr++ = ' ';
2502
2503 memcpy( ptr, data, len );
2504 fs->buffer = ptr + len;
2505 }
2506}

2526
2527static void
2528icvXMLWriteString( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* key, const char* str, int quote )
2529{
2530 char buf[CV_FS_MAX_LEN*6+16];
2531 char* data = (char*)str;
2532 int i, len;
2533
2534 if( !str )
2535 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null string pointer" );
2536
2537 len = (int)strlen(str);
2538 if( len > CV_FS_MAX_LEN )
2539 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "The written string is too long" );
2540
2541 if( quote || len == 0 || str[0] != '\"' || str[0] != str[len-1] )
2542 {
2543 int need_quote = quote || len == 0;
2544 data = buf;
2545 *data++ = '\"';
2546 for( i = 0; i < len; i++ )
2547 {
2548 char c = str[i];
2549
2550 if( (uchar)c >= 128 || c == ' ' )
2551 {
2552 *data++ = c;
2553 need_quote = 1;
2554 }
2555 else if( !cv_isprint(c) || c == '<' || c == '>' || c == '&' || c == '\'' || c == '\"' )
2556 {
2557 *data++ = '&';
2558 if( c == '<' )
2559 {
2560 memcpy(data, "lt", 2);
2561 data += 2;
2562 }
2563 else if( c == '>' )
2564 {
2565 memcpy(data, "gt", 2);
2566 data += 2;
2567 }
2568 else if( c == '&' )
2569 {
2570 memcpy(data, "amp", 3);
2571 data += 3;
2572 }
2573 else if( c == '\'' )
2574 {
2575 memcpy(data, "apos", 4);
2576 data += 4;
2577 }
2578 else if( c == '\"' )
2579 {
2580 memcpy( data, "quot", 4);
2581 data += 4;
2582 }
2583 else
2584 {
2585 sprintf( data, "#x%02x", (uchar)c );
2586 data += 4;
2587 }
2588 *data++ = ';';
2589 need_quote = 1;
2590 }
2591 else
2592 *data++ = c;
2593 }
2594 if( !need_quote && (cv_isdigit(str[0]) ||
2595 str[0] == '+' || str[0] == '-' || str[0] == '.' ))
2596 need_quote = 1;
2597
2598 if( need_quote )
2599 *data++ = '\"';
2600 len = (int)(data - buf) - !need_quote;
2601 *data++ = '\0';
2602 data = buf + !need_quote;
2603 }
2604
2605 icvXMLWriteScalar( fs, key, data, len );
2606}

2608
2609static void
2610icvXMLWriteComment( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* comment, int eol_comment )
2611{
2612 int len;
2613 int multiline;
2614 const char* eol;
2615 char* ptr;
2616
2617 if( !comment )
2618 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null comment" );
2619
2620 if( strstr(comment, "--") != 0 )
2621 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Double hyphen \'--\' is not allowed in the comments" );
2622
2623 len = (int)strlen(comment);
2624 eol = strchr(comment, '\n');
2625 multiline = eol != 0;
2626 ptr = fs->buffer;
2627
2628 if( multiline || !eol_comment || fs->buffer_end - ptr < len + 5 )
2629 ptr = icvXMLFlush( fs );
2630 else if( ptr > fs->buffer_start + fs->struct_indent )
2631 *ptr++ = ' ';
2632
2633 if( !multiline )
2634 {
2635 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, len + 9 );
2636 sprintf( ptr, "<!-- %s -->", comment );
2637 len = (int)strlen(ptr);
2638 }
2639 else
2640 {
2641 strcpy( ptr, "<!--" );
2642 len = 4;
2643 }
2644
2645 fs->buffer = ptr + len;
2646 ptr = icvXMLFlush(fs);
2647
2648 if( multiline )
2649 {
2650 while( comment )
2651 {
2652 if( eol )
2653 {
2654 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, (int)(eol - comment) + 1 );
2655 memcpy( ptr, comment, eol - comment + 1 );
2656 ptr += eol - comment;
2657 comment = eol + 1;
2658 eol = strchr( comment, '\n' );
2659 }
2660 else
2661 {
2662 len = (int)strlen(comment);
2663 ptr = icvFSResizeWriteBuffer( fs, ptr, len );
2664 memcpy( ptr, comment, len );
2665 ptr += len;
2666 comment = 0;
2667 }
2668 fs->buffer = ptr;
2669 ptr = icvXMLFlush( fs );
2670 }
2671 sprintf( ptr, "-->" );
2672 fs->buffer = ptr + 3;
2673 icvXMLFlush( fs );
2674 }
2675}

2678/****************************************************************************************\
2679* Common High-Level Functions *
2680\****************************************************************************************/
2681
2682CV_IMPL CvFileStorage*
2683cvOpenFileStorage( const char* filename, CvMemStorage* dststorage, int flags, const char* encoding )
2684{
2685 CvFileStorage* fs = 0;
2686 int default_block_size = 1 << 18;
2687 bool append = (flags & 3) == CV_STORAGE_APPEND;
2688 bool mem = (flags & CV_STORAGE_MEMORY) != 0;
2689 bool write_mode = (flags & 3) != 0;
2690 bool isGZ = false;
2691 size_t fnamelen = 0;
2692
2693 if( !filename || filename[0] == '\0' )
2694 {
2695 if( !write_mode )
2696 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, mem ? "NULL or empty filename" : "NULL or empty buffer" );
2697 mem = true;
2698 }
2699 else
2700 fnamelen = strlen(filename);
2701
2702 if( mem && append )
2703 CV_Error( CV_StsBadFlag, "CV_STORAGE_APPEND and CV_STORAGE_MEMORY are not currently compatible" );
2704
2705 fs = (CvFileStorage*)cvAlloc( sizeof(*fs) );
2706 memset( fs, 0, sizeof(*fs));
2707
2708 fs->memstorage = cvCreateMemStorage( default_block_size );
2709 fs->dststorage = dststorage ? dststorage : fs->memstorage;
2710
2711 fs->flags = CV_FILE_STORAGE;
2712 fs->write_mode = write_mode;
2713
2714 if( !mem )
2715 {
2716 fs->filename = (char*)cvMemStorageAlloc( fs->memstorage, fnamelen+1 );
2717 strcpy( fs->filename, filename );
2718
2719 char* dot_pos = strrchr(fs->filename, '.');
2720 char compression = '\0';
2721
2722 if( dot_pos && dot_pos[1] == 'g' && dot_pos[2] == 'z' &&
2723 (dot_pos[3] == '\0' || (cv_isdigit(dot_pos[3]) && dot_pos[4] == '\0')) )
2724 {
2725 if( append )
2726 {
2727 cvReleaseFileStorage( &fs );
2728 CV_Error(CV_StsNotImplemented, "Appending data to compressed file is not implemented" );
2729 }
2730 isGZ = true;
2731 compression = dot_pos[3];
2732 if( compression )
2733 dot_pos[3] = '\0', fnamelen--;
2734 }
2735
2736 if( !isGZ )
2737 {
2738 fs->file = fopen(fs->filename, !fs->write_mode ? "rt" : !append ? "wt" : "a+t" );
2739 if( !fs->file )
2740 goto _exit_;
2741 }
2742 else
2743 {
2744 #if USE_ZLIB
2745 char mode[] = { fs->write_mode ? 'w' : 'r', 'b', compression ? compression : '3', '\0' };
2746 fs->gzfile = gzopen(fs->filename, mode);
2747 if( !fs->gzfile )
2748 goto _exit_;
2749 #else
2750 cvReleaseFileStorage( &fs );
2751 CV_Error(CV_StsNotImplemented, "There is no compressed file storage support in this configuration");
2752 #endif
2753 }
2754 }
2755
2756 fs->roots = 0;
2757 fs->struct_indent = 0;
2758 fs->struct_flags = 0;
2759 fs->wrap_margin = 71;
2760
2761 if( fs->write_mode )
2762 {
2763 int fmt = flags & CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_MASK;
2764
2765 if( mem )
2766 fs->outbuf = new std::deque<char>;
2767
2768 if( fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_AUTO && filename )
2769 {
2770 const char* dot_pos = filename + fnamelen - (isGZ ? 7 : 4);
2771 fs->fmt = (dot_pos >= filename && (memcmp( dot_pos, ".xml", 4) == 0 ||
2772 memcmp(dot_pos, ".XML", 4) == 0 || memcmp(dot_pos, ".Xml", 4) == 0)) ?
2773 CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML : CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_YAML;
2774 }
2775 else
2776 fs->fmt = fmt != CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_AUTO ? fmt : CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML;
2777
2778 // we use factor=6 for XML (the longest characters (' and ") are encoded with 6 bytes (&apos; and &quot;)
2779 // and factor=4 for YAML ( as we use 4 bytes for non ASCII characters (e.g. \xAB))
2780 int buf_size = CV_FS_MAX_LEN*(fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML ? 6 : 4) + 1024;
2781
2782 if( append )
2783 fseek( fs->file, 0, SEEK_END );
2784
2785 fs->write_stack = cvCreateSeq( 0, sizeof(CvSeq), fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML ?
2786 sizeof(CvXMLStackRecord) : sizeof(int), fs->memstorage );
2787 fs->is_first = 1;
2788 fs->struct_indent = 0;
2789 fs->struct_flags = CV_NODE_EMPTY;
2790 fs->buffer_start = fs->buffer = (char*)cvAlloc( buf_size + 1024 );
2791 fs->buffer_end = fs->buffer_start + buf_size;
2792 if( fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML )
2793 {
2794 size_t file_size = fs->file ? (size_t)ftell( fs->file ) : (size_t)0;
2795 fs->strstorage = cvCreateChildMemStorage( fs->memstorage );
2796 if( !append || file_size == 0 )
2797 {
2798 if( encoding )
2799 {
2800 if( strcmp( encoding, "UTF-16" ) == 0 ||
2801 strcmp( encoding, "utf-16" ) == 0 ||
2802 strcmp( encoding, "Utf-16" ) == 0 )
2803 {
2804 cvReleaseFileStorage( &fs );
2805 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "UTF-16 XML encoding is not supported! Use 8-bit encoding\n");
2806 }
2807
2808 CV_Assert( strlen(encoding) < 1000 );
2809 char buf[1100];
2810 sprintf(buf, "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"%s\"?>\n", encoding);
2811 icvPuts( fs, buf );
2812 }
2813 else
2814 icvPuts( fs, "<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n" );
2815 icvPuts( fs, "<opencv_storage>\n" );
2816 }
2817 else
2818 {
2819 int xml_buf_size = 1 << 10;
2820 char substr[] = "</opencv_storage>";
2821 int last_occurence = -1;
2822 xml_buf_size = MIN(xml_buf_size, int(file_size));
2823 fseek( fs->file, -xml_buf_size, SEEK_END );
2824 char* xml_buf = (char*)cvAlloc( xml_buf_size+2 );
2825 // find the last occurence of </opencv_storage>
2826 for(;;)
2827 {
2828 int line_offset = (int)ftell( fs->file );
2829 char* ptr0 = icvGets( fs, xml_buf, xml_buf_size ), *ptr;
2830 if( !ptr0 )
2831 break;
2832 ptr = ptr0;
2833 for(;;)
2834 {
2835 ptr = strstr( ptr, substr );
2836 if( !ptr )
2837 break;
2838 last_occurence = line_offset + (int)(ptr - ptr0);
2839 ptr += strlen(substr);
2840 }
2841 }
2842 cvFree( &xml_buf );
2843 if( last_occurence < 0 )
2844 {
2845 cvReleaseFileStorage( &fs );
2846 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Could not find </opencv_storage> in the end of file.\n" );
2847 }
2848 icvCloseFile( fs );
2849 fs->file = fopen( fs->filename, "r+t" );
2850 fseek( fs->file, last_occurence, SEEK_SET );
2851 // replace the last "</opencv_storage>" with " <!-- resumed -->", which has the same length
2852 icvPuts( fs, " <!-- resumed -->" );
2853 fseek( fs->file, 0, SEEK_END );
2854 icvPuts( fs, "\n" );
2855 }
2856 fs->start_write_struct = icvXMLStartWriteStruct;
2857 fs->end_write_struct = icvXMLEndWriteStruct;
2858 fs->write_int = icvXMLWriteInt;
2859 fs->write_real = icvXMLWriteReal;
2860 fs->write_string = icvXMLWriteString;
2861 fs->write_comment = icvXMLWriteComment;
2862 fs->start_next_stream = icvXMLStartNextStream;
2863 }
2864 else
2865 {
2866 if( !append )
2867 icvPuts( fs, "%YAML:1.0\n" );
2868 else
2869 icvPuts( fs, "...\n---\n" );
2870 fs->start_write_struct = icvYMLStartWriteStruct;
2871 fs->end_write_struct = icvYMLEndWriteStruct;
2872 fs->write_int = icvYMLWriteInt;
2873 fs->write_real = icvYMLWriteReal;
2874 fs->write_string = icvYMLWriteString;
2875 fs->write_comment = icvYMLWriteComment;
2876 fs->start_next_stream = icvYMLStartNextStream;
2877 }
2878 }
2879 else
2880 {
2881 if( mem )
2882 {
2883 fs->strbuf = filename;
2884 fs->strbufsize = fnamelen;
2885 }
2886
2887 size_t buf_size = 1 << 20;
2888 const char* yaml_signature = "%YAML:";
2889 char buf[16];
2890 icvGets( fs, buf, sizeof(buf)-2 );
2891 fs->fmt = strncmp( buf, yaml_signature, strlen(yaml_signature) ) == 0 ?
2892 CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_YAML : CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML;
2893
2894 if( !isGZ )
2895 {
2896 if( !mem )
2897 {
2898 fseek( fs->file, 0, SEEK_END );
2899 buf_size = ftell( fs->file );
2900 }
2901 else
2902 buf_size = fs->strbufsize;
2903 buf_size = MIN( buf_size, (size_t)(1 << 20) );
2904 buf_size = MAX( buf_size, (size_t)(CV_FS_MAX_LEN*2 + 1024) );
2905 }
2906 icvRewind(fs);
2907
2908 fs->str_hash = cvCreateMap( 0, sizeof(CvStringHash),
2909 sizeof(CvStringHashNode), fs->memstorage, 256 );
2910
2911 fs->roots = cvCreateSeq( 0, sizeof(CvSeq),
2912 sizeof(CvFileNode), fs->memstorage );
2913
2914 fs->buffer = fs->buffer_start = (char*)cvAlloc( buf_size + 256 );
2915 fs->buffer_end = fs->buffer_start + buf_size;
2916 fs->buffer[0] = '\n';
2917 fs->buffer[1] = '\0';
2918
2919 //mode = cvGetErrMode();
2920 //cvSetErrMode( CV_ErrModeSilent );
2921 try
2922 {
2923 if( fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML )
2924 icvXMLParse( fs );
2925 else
2926 icvYMLParse( fs );
2927 }
2928 catch (...)
2929 {
2930 cvReleaseFileStorage( &fs );
2931 throw;
2932 }
2933 //cvSetErrMode( mode );
2934
2935 // release resources that we do not need anymore
2936 cvFree( &fs->buffer_start );
2937 fs->buffer = fs->buffer_end = 0;
2938 }
2939 fs->is_opened = true;
2940
2941_exit_:
2942 if( fs )
2943 {
2944 if( cvGetErrStatus() < 0 || (!fs->file && !fs->gzfile && !fs->outbuf && !fs->strbuf) )
2945 {
2946 cvReleaseFileStorage( &fs );
2947 }
2948 else if( !fs->write_mode )
2949 {
2950 icvCloseFile(fs);
2951 // we close the file since it's not needed anymore. But icvCloseFile() resets is_opened,
2952 // which may be misleading. Since we restore the value of is_opened.
2953 fs->is_opened = true;
2954 }
2955 }
2956
2957 return fs;
2958}

3018static const char icvTypeSymbol[] = "ucwsifdr";
3019#define CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS 128
3020
3021static char*
3022icvEncodeFormat( int elem_type, char* dt )
3023{
3024 sprintf( dt, "%d%c", CV_MAT_CN(elem_type), icvTypeSymbol[CV_MAT_DEPTH(elem_type)] );
3025 return dt + ( dt[2] == '\0' && dt[0] == '1' );
3026}
3027
3028static int
3029icvDecodeFormat( const char* dt, int* fmt_pairs, int max_len )
3030{
3031 int fmt_pair_count = 0;
3032 int i = 0, k = 0, len = dt ? (int)strlen(dt) : 0;
3033
3034 if( !dt || !len )
3035 return 0;
3036
3037 assert( fmt_pairs != 0 && max_len > 0 );
3038 fmt_pairs[0] = 0;
3039 max_len *= 2;
3040
3041 for( ; k < len; k++ )
3042 {
3043 char c = dt[k];
3044
3045 if( cv_isdigit(c) )
3046 {
3047 int count = c - '0';
3048 if( cv_isdigit(dt[k+1]) )
3049 {
3050 char* endptr = 0;
3051 count = (int)strtol( dt+k, &endptr, 10 );
3052 k = (int)(endptr - dt) - 1;
3053 }
3054
3055 if( count <= 0 )
3056 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Invalid data type specification" );
3057
3058 fmt_pairs[i] = count;
3059 }
3060 else
3061 {
3062 const char* pos = strchr( icvTypeSymbol, c );
3063 if( !pos )
3064 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Invalid data type specification" );
3065 if( fmt_pairs[i] == 0 )
3066 fmt_pairs[i] = 1;
3067 fmt_pairs[i+1] = (int)(pos - icvTypeSymbol);
3068 if( i > 0 && fmt_pairs[i+1] == fmt_pairs[i-1] )
3069 fmt_pairs[i-2] += fmt_pairs[i];
3070 else
3071 {
3072 i += 2;
3073 if( i >= max_len )
3074 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Too long data type specification" );
3075 }
3076 fmt_pairs[i] = 0;
3077 }
3078 }
3079
3080 fmt_pair_count = i/2;
3081 return fmt_pair_count;
3082}
3083
3084
3085static int
3086icvCalcElemSize( const char* dt, int initial_size )
3087{
3088 int size = 0;
3089 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS], i, fmt_pair_count;
3090 int comp_size;
3091
3092 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( dt, fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
3093 fmt_pair_count *= 2;
3094 for( i = 0, size = initial_size; i < fmt_pair_count; i += 2 )
3095 {
3096 comp_size = CV_ELEM_SIZE(fmt_pairs[i+1]);
3097 size = cvAlign( size, comp_size );
3098 size += comp_size * fmt_pairs[i];
3099 }
3100 if( initial_size == 0 )
3101 {
3102 comp_size = CV_ELEM_SIZE(fmt_pairs[1]);
3103 size = cvAlign( size, comp_size );
3104 }
3105 return size;
3106}

3109static int
3110icvDecodeSimpleFormat( const char* dt )
3111{
3112 int elem_type = -1;
3113 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS], fmt_pair_count;
3114
3115 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( dt, fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
3116 if( fmt_pair_count != 1 || fmt_pairs[0] > 4 )
3117 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Too complex format for the matrix" );
3118
3119 elem_type = CV_MAKETYPE( fmt_pairs[1], fmt_pairs[0] );
3120
3121 return elem_type;
3122}

3125CV_IMPL void
3126cvWriteRawData( CvFileStorage* fs, const void* _data, int len, const char* dt )
3127{
3128 const char* data0 = (const char*)_data;
3129 int offset = 0;
3130 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS*2], k, fmt_pair_count;
3131 char buf[256] = "";
3132
3133 CV_CHECK_OUTPUT_FILE_STORAGE( fs );
3134
3135 if( len < 0 )
3136 CV_Error( CV_StsOutOfRange, "Negative number of elements" );
3137
3138 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( dt, fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
3139
3140 if( !len )
3141 return;
3142
3143 if( !data0 )
3144 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null data pointer" );
3145
3146 if( fmt_pair_count == 1 )
3147 {
3148 fmt_pairs[0] *= len;
3149 len = 1;
3150 }
3151
3152 for(;len--;)
3153 {
3154 for( k = 0; k < fmt_pair_count; k++ )
3155 {
3156 int i, count = fmt_pairs[k*2];
3157 int elem_type = fmt_pairs[k*2+1];
3158 int elem_size = CV_ELEM_SIZE(elem_type);
3159 const char* data, *ptr;
3160
3161 offset = cvAlign( offset, elem_size );
3162 data = data0 + offset;
3163
3164 for( i = 0; i < count; i++ )
3165 {
3166 switch( elem_type )
3167 {
3168 case CV_8U:
3169 ptr = icv_itoa( *(uchar*)data, buf, 10 );
3170 data++;
3171 break;
3172 case CV_8S:
3173 ptr = icv_itoa( *(char*)data, buf, 10 );
3174 data++;
3175 break;
3176 case CV_16U:
3177 ptr = icv_itoa( *(ushort*)data, buf, 10 );
3178 data += sizeof(ushort);
3179 break;
3180 case CV_16S:
3181 ptr = icv_itoa( *(short*)data, buf, 10 );
3182 data += sizeof(short);
3183 break;
3184 case CV_32S:
3185 ptr = icv_itoa( *(int*)data, buf, 10 );
3186 data += sizeof(int);
3187 break;
3188 case CV_32F:
3189 ptr = icvFloatToString( buf, *(float*)data );
3190 data += sizeof(float);
3191 break;
3192 case CV_64F:
3193 ptr = icvDoubleToString( buf, *(double*)data );
3194 data += sizeof(double);
3195 break;
3196 case CV_USRTYPE1: /* reference */
3197 ptr = icv_itoa( (int)*(size_t*)data, buf, 10 );
3198 data += sizeof(size_t);
3199 break;
3200 default:
3201 assert(0);
3202 return;
3203 }
3204
3205 if( fs->fmt == CV_STORAGE_FORMAT_XML )
3206 {
3207 int buf_len = (int)strlen(ptr);
3208 icvXMLWriteScalar( fs, 0, ptr, buf_len );
3209 }
3210 else
3211 icvYMLWrite( fs, 0, ptr );
3212 }
3213
3214 offset = (int)(data - data0);
3215 }
3216 }
3217}

3221cvStartReadRawData( const CvFileStorage* fs, const CvFileNode* src, CvSeqReader* reader )
3222{
3223 int node_type;
3224 CV_CHECK_FILE_STORAGE( fs );
3225
3226 if( !src || !reader )
3227 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null pointer to source file node or reader" );
3228
3229 node_type = CV_NODE_TYPE(src->tag);
3230 if( node_type == CV_NODE_INT || node_type == CV_NODE_REAL )
3231 {
3232 // emulate reading from 1-element sequence
3233 reader->ptr = (schar*)src;
3234 reader->block_max = reader->ptr + sizeof(*src)*2;
3235 reader->block_min = reader->ptr;
3236 reader->seq = 0;
3237 }
3238 else if( node_type == CV_NODE_SEQ )
3239 {
3240 cvStartReadSeq( src->data.seq, reader, 0 );
3241 }
3242 else if( node_type == CV_NODE_NONE )
3243 {
3244 memset( reader, 0, sizeof(*reader) );
3245 }
3246 else
3247 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "The file node should be a numerical scalar or a sequence" );
3248}

3251CV_IMPL void
3252cvReadRawDataSlice( const CvFileStorage* fs, CvSeqReader* reader,
3253 int len, void* _data, const char* dt )
3254{
3255 char* data0 = (char*)_data;
3256 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS*2], k = 0, fmt_pair_count;
3257 int i = 0, offset = 0, count = 0;
3258
3259 CV_CHECK_FILE_STORAGE( fs );
3260
3261 if( !reader || !data0 )
3262 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr, "Null pointer to reader or destination array" );
3263
3264 if( !reader->seq && len != 1 )
3265 CV_Error( CV_StsBadSize, "The readed sequence is a scalar, thus len must be 1" );
3266
3267 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( dt, fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
3268
3269 for(;;)
3270 {
3271 for( k = 0; k < fmt_pair_count; k++ )
3272 {
3273 int elem_type = fmt_pairs[k*2+1];
3274 int elem_size = CV_ELEM_SIZE(elem_type);
3275 char* data;
3276
3277 count = fmt_pairs[k*2];
3278 offset = cvAlign( offset, elem_size );
3279 data = data0 + offset;
3280
3281 for( i = 0; i < count; i++ )
3282 {
3283 CvFileNode* node = (CvFileNode*)reader->ptr;
3284 if( CV_NODE_IS_INT(node->tag) )
3285 {
3286 int ival = node->data.i;
3287
3288 switch( elem_type )
3289 {
3290 case CV_8U:
3291 *(uchar*)data = CV_CAST_8U(ival);
3292 data++;
3293 break;
3294 case CV_8S:
3295 *(char*)data = CV_CAST_8S(ival);
3296 data++;
3297 break;
3298 case CV_16U:
3299 *(ushort*)data = CV_CAST_16U(ival);
3300 data += sizeof(ushort);
3301 break;
3302 case CV_16S:
3303 *(short*)data = CV_CAST_16S(ival);
3304 data += sizeof(short);
3305 break;
3306 case CV_32S:
3307 *(int*)data = ival;
3308 data += sizeof(int);
3309 break;
3310 case CV_32F:
3311 *(float*)data = (float)ival;
3312 data += sizeof(float);
3313 break;
3314 case CV_64F:
3315 *(double*)data = (double)ival;
3316 data += sizeof(double);
3317 break;
3318 case CV_USRTYPE1: /* reference */
3319 *(size_t*)data = ival;
3320 data += sizeof(size_t);
3321 break;
3322 default:
3323 assert(0);
3324 return;
3325 }
3326 }
3327 else if( CV_NODE_IS_REAL(node->tag) )
3328 {
3329 double fval = node->data.f;
3330 int ival;
3331
3332 switch( elem_type )
3333 {
3334 case CV_8U:
3335 ival = cvRound(fval);
3336 *(uchar*)data = CV_CAST_8U(ival);
3337 data++;
3338 break;
3339 case CV_8S:
3340 ival = cvRound(fval);
3341 *(char*)data = CV_CAST_8S(ival);
3342 data++;
3343 break;
3344 case CV_16U:
3345 ival = cvRound(fval);
3346 *(ushort*)data = CV_CAST_16U(ival);
3347 data += sizeof(ushort);
3348 break;
3349 case CV_16S:
3350 ival = cvRound(fval);
3351 *(short*)data = CV_CAST_16S(ival);
3352 data += sizeof(short);
3353 break;
3354 case CV_32S:
3355 ival = cvRound(fval);
3356 *(int*)data = ival;
3357 data += sizeof(int);
3358 break;
3359 case CV_32F:
3360 *(float*)data = (float)fval;
3361 data += sizeof(float);
3362 break;
3363 case CV_64F:
3364 *(double*)data = fval;
3365 data += sizeof(double);
3366 break;
3367 case CV_USRTYPE1: /* reference */
3368 ival = cvRound(fval);
3369 *(size_t*)data = ival;
3370 data += sizeof(size_t);
3371 break;
3372 default:
3373 assert(0);
3374 return;
3375 }
3376 }
3377 else
3378 CV_Error( CV_StsError,
3379 "The sequence element is not a numerical scalar" );
3380
3381 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( sizeof(CvFileNode), *reader );
3382 if( !--len )
3383 goto end_loop;
3384 }
3385
3386 offset = (int)(data - data0);
3387 }
3388 }
3389
3390end_loop:
3391 if( i != count - 1 || k != fmt_pair_count - 1 )
3392 CV_Error( CV_StsBadSize,
3393 "The sequence slice does not fit an integer number of records" );
3394
3395 if( !reader->seq )
3396 reader->ptr -= sizeof(CvFileNode);
3397}

3423 int is_map = CV_NODE_IS_MAP(node->tag);

3441icvWriteFileNode( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* name, const CvFileNode* node )
3442{

3444 {
3445 case CV_NODE_INT:
3446 fs->write_int( fs, name, node->data.i );
3447 break;
3448 case CV_NODE_REAL:
3449 fs->write_real( fs, name, node->data.f );
3450 break;
3451 case CV_NODE_STR:
3452 fs->write_string( fs, name, node->data.str.ptr, 0 );
3453 break;
3454 case CV_NODE_SEQ:
3455 case CV_NODE_MAP:
3456 fs->start_write_struct( fs, name, CV_NODE_TYPE(node->tag) +
3457 (CV_NODE_SEQ_IS_SIMPLE(node->data.seq) ? CV_NODE_FLOW : 0),
3458 node->info ? node->info->type_name : 0 );
3459 icvWriteCollection( fs, node );
3460 fs->end_write_struct( fs );
3461 break;
3462 case CV_NODE_NONE:
3463 fs->start_write_struct( fs, name, CV_NODE_SEQ, 0 );
3464 fs->end_write_struct( fs );
3465 break;
3466 default:
3467 CV_Error( CV_StsBadFlag, "Unknown type of file node" );
3468 }

3546 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "data", CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );

3548 size = cvGetSize(mat);
3549 if( size.height > 0 && size.width > 0 && mat->data.ptr )
3550 {
3551 if( CV_IS_MAT_CONT(mat->type) )
3552 {
3553 size.width *= size.height;
3554 size.height = 1;
3555 }
3556
3557 for( y = 0; y < size.height; y++ )
3558 cvWriteRawData( fs, mat->data.ptr + (size_t)y*mat->step, size.width, dt );
3559 }
3560 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3561 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3562}

3719
3720static int
3721icvSortIdxCmpFunc( const void* _a, const void* _b, void* userdata )
3722{
3723 int i, dims = *(int*)userdata;
3724 const int* a = *(const int**)_a;
3725 const int* b = *(const int**)_b;
3726
3727 for( i = 0; i < dims; i++ )
3728 {
3729 int delta = a[i] - b[i];
3730 if( delta )
3731 return delta;
3732 }
3733
3734 return 0;
3735}
