3738static void
3739icvWriteSparseMat( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* name,
3740 const void* struct_ptr, CvAttrList /*attr*/ )
3741{
3742 CvMemStorage* memstorage = 0;
3743 const CvSparseMat* mat = (const CvSparseMat*)struct_ptr;
3744 CvSparseMatIterator iterator;
3745 CvSparseNode* node;
3746 CvSeq* elements;
3747 CvSeqReader reader;
3748 int i, dims;
3749 int *prev_idx = 0;
3750 char dt[16];
3751
3752 assert( CV_IS_SPARSE_MAT(mat) );
3753
3754 memstorage = cvCreateMemStorage();
3755
3756 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, name, CV_NODE_MAP, CV_TYPE_NAME_SPARSE_MAT );
3757 dims = cvGetDims( mat, 0 );
3758
3759 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "sizes", CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );
3760 cvWriteRawData( fs, mat->size, dims, "i" );
3761 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3762 cvWriteString( fs, "dt", icvEncodeFormat( CV_MAT_TYPE(mat->type), dt ), 0 );
3763 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "data", CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );
3764
3765 elements = cvCreateSeq( CV_SEQ_ELTYPE_PTR, sizeof(CvSeq), sizeof(int*), memstorage );
3766
3767 node = cvInitSparseMatIterator( mat, &iterator );
3768 while( node )
3769 {
3770 int* idx = CV_NODE_IDX( mat, node );
3771 cvSeqPush( elements, &idx );
3772 node = cvGetNextSparseNode( &iterator );
3773 }
3774
3775 cvSeqSort( elements, icvSortIdxCmpFunc, &dims );
3776 cvStartReadSeq( elements, &reader, 0 );
3777
3778 for( i = 0; i < elements->total; i++ )
3779 {
3780 int* idx;
3781 void* val;
3782 int k = 0;
3783
3784 CV_READ_SEQ_ELEM( idx, reader );
3785 if( i > 0 )
3786 {
3787 for( ; idx[k] == prev_idx[k]; k++ )
3788 assert( k < dims );
3789 if( k < dims - 1 )
3790 fs->write_int( fs, 0, k - dims + 1 );
3791 }
3792 for( ; k < dims; k++ )
3793 fs->write_int( fs, 0, idx[k] );
3794 prev_idx = idx;
3795
3796 node = (CvSparseNode*)((uchar*)idx - mat->idxoffset );
3797 val = CV_NODE_VAL( mat, node );
3798
3799 cvWriteRawData( fs, val, 1, dt );
3800 }
3801
3802 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3803 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3804 cvReleaseMemStorage( &memstorage );
3805}

3808static void*
3809icvReadSparseMat( CvFileStorage* fs, CvFileNode* node )
3810{
3811 void* ptr = 0;
3812 CvSparseMat* mat;
3813 const char* dt;
3814 CvFileNode* data;
3815 CvFileNode* sizes_node;
3816 CvSeqReader reader;
3817 CvSeq* elements;
3818 int sizes[CV_MAX_DIM_HEAP], dims, elem_type, cn;
3819 int i;
3820
3821 sizes_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "sizes" );
3822 dt = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "dt", 0 );
3823
3824 if( !sizes_node || !dt )
3825 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Some of essential matrix attributes are absent" );
3826
3827 dims = CV_NODE_IS_SEQ(sizes_node->tag) ? sizes_node->data.seq->total :
3828 CV_NODE_IS_INT(sizes_node->tag) ? 1 : -1;
3829
3830 if( dims <= 0 || dims > CV_MAX_DIM_HEAP )
3831 CV_Error( CV_StsParseError, "Could not determine sparse matrix dimensionality" );
3832
3833 cvReadRawData( fs, sizes_node, sizes, "i" );
3834 elem_type = icvDecodeSimpleFormat( dt );
3835
3836 data = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "data" );
3837 if( !data || !CV_NODE_IS_SEQ(data->tag) )
3838 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The matrix data is not found in file storage" );
3839
3840 mat = cvCreateSparseMat( dims, sizes, elem_type );
3841
3842 cn = CV_MAT_CN(elem_type);
3843 int idx[CV_MAX_DIM_HEAP];
3844 elements = data->data.seq;
3845 cvStartReadRawData( fs, data, &reader );
3846
3847 for( i = 0; i < elements->total; )
3848 {
3849 CvFileNode* elem = (CvFileNode*)reader.ptr;
3850 uchar* val;
3851 int k;
3852 if( !CV_NODE_IS_INT(elem->tag ))
3853 CV_Error( CV_StsParseError, "Sparse matrix data is corrupted" );
3854 k = elem->data.i;
3855 if( i > 0 && k >= 0 )
3856 idx[dims-1] = k;
3857 else
3858 {
3859 if( i > 0 )
3860 k = dims + k - 1;
3861 else
3862 idx[0] = k, k = 1;
3863 for( ; k < dims; k++ )
3864 {
3865 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( elements->elem_size, reader );
3866 i++;
3867 elem = (CvFileNode*)reader.ptr;
3868 if( !CV_NODE_IS_INT(elem->tag ) || elem->data.i < 0 )
3869 CV_Error( CV_StsParseError, "Sparse matrix data is corrupted" );
3870 idx[k] = elem->data.i;
3871 }
3872 }
3873 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( elements->elem_size, reader );
3874 i++;
3875 val = cvPtrND( mat, idx, 0, 1, 0 );
3876 cvReadRawDataSlice( fs, &reader, cn, val, dt );
3877 i += cn;
3878 }
3879
3880 ptr = mat;
3881 return ptr;
3882}

3896{
3897 const IplImage* image = (const IplImage*)struct_ptr;
3898 char dt_buf[16], *dt;
3899 CvSize size;
3900 int y, depth;
3901
3902 assert( CV_IS_IMAGE(image) );
3903
3904 if( image->dataOrder == IPL_DATA_ORDER_PLANE )
3905 CV_Error( CV_StsUnsupportedFormat,
3906 "Images with planar data layout are not supported" );
3907
3908 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, name, CV_NODE_MAP, CV_TYPE_NAME_IMAGE );
3909 cvWriteInt( fs, "width", image->width );
3910 cvWriteInt( fs, "height", image->height );
3911 cvWriteString( fs, "origin", image->origin == IPL_ORIGIN_TL
3912 ? "top-left" : "bottom-left", 0 );
3913 cvWriteString( fs, "layout", image->dataOrder == IPL_DATA_ORDER_PLANE
3914 ? "planar" : "interleaved", 0 );
3915 if( image->roi )
3916 {
3917 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "roi", CV_NODE_MAP + CV_NODE_FLOW );
3918 cvWriteInt( fs, "x", image->roi->xOffset );
3919 cvWriteInt( fs, "y", image->roi->yOffset );
3920 cvWriteInt( fs, "width", image->roi->width );
3921 cvWriteInt( fs, "height", image->roi->height );
3922 cvWriteInt( fs, "coi", image->roi->coi );
3923 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3924 }
3925
3926 depth = IPL2CV_DEPTH(image->depth);
3927 sprintf( dt_buf, "%d%c", image->nChannels, icvTypeSymbol[depth] );
3928 dt = dt_buf + (dt_buf[2] == '\0' && dt_buf[0] == '1');
3929 cvWriteString( fs, "dt", dt, 0 );
3930
3931 size = cvSize(image->width, image->height);
3932 if( size.width*image->nChannels*CV_ELEM_SIZE(depth) == image->widthStep )
3933 {
3934 size.width *= size.height;
3935 size.height = 1;
3936 }
3937
3938 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "data", CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );
3939 for( y = 0; y < size.height; y++ )
3940 cvWriteRawData( fs, image->imageData + y*image->widthStep, size.width, dt );
3941 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3942 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
3943}

4040
4041static void
4042icvWriteHeaderData( CvFileStorage* fs, const CvSeq* seq,
4043 CvAttrList* attr, int initial_header_size )
4044{
4045 char header_dt_buf[128];
4046 const char* header_dt = cvAttrValue( attr, "header_dt" );
4047
4048 if( header_dt )
4049 {
4050 int dt_header_size;
4051 dt_header_size = icvCalcElemSize( header_dt, initial_header_size );
4052 if( dt_header_size > seq->header_size )
4053 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
4054 "The size of header calculated from \"header_dt\" is greater than header_size" );
4055 }
4056 else if( seq->header_size > initial_header_size )
4057 {
4058 if( CV_IS_SEQ(seq) && CV_IS_SEQ_POINT_SET(seq) &&
4059 seq->header_size == sizeof(CvPoint2DSeq) &&
4060 seq->elem_size == sizeof(int)*2 )
4061 {
4062 CvPoint2DSeq* point_seq = (CvPoint2DSeq*)seq;
4063
4064 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "rect", CV_NODE_MAP + CV_NODE_FLOW );
4065 cvWriteInt( fs, "x", point_seq->rect.x );
4066 cvWriteInt( fs, "y", point_seq->rect.y );
4067 cvWriteInt( fs, "width", point_seq->rect.width );
4068 cvWriteInt( fs, "height", point_seq->rect.height );
4069 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4070 cvWriteInt( fs, "color", point_seq->color );
4071 }
4072 else if( CV_IS_SEQ(seq) && CV_IS_SEQ_CHAIN(seq) &&
4073 CV_MAT_TYPE(seq->flags) == CV_8UC1 )
4074 {
4075 CvChain* chain = (CvChain*)seq;
4076
4077 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "origin", CV_NODE_MAP + CV_NODE_FLOW );
4078 cvWriteInt( fs, "x", chain->origin.x );
4079 cvWriteInt( fs, "y", chain->origin.y );
4080 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4081 }
4082 else
4083 {
4084 unsigned extra_size = seq->header_size - initial_header_size;
4085 // a heuristic to provide nice defaults for sequences of int's & float's
4086 if( extra_size % sizeof(int) == 0 )
4087 sprintf( header_dt_buf, "%ui", (unsigned)(extra_size/sizeof(int)) );
4088 else
4089 sprintf( header_dt_buf, "%uu", extra_size );
4090 header_dt = header_dt_buf;
4091 }
4092 }
4093
4094 if( header_dt )
4095 {
4096 cvWriteString( fs, "header_dt", header_dt, 0 );
4097 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "header_user_data", CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );
4098 cvWriteRawData( fs, (uchar*)seq + sizeof(CvSeq), 1, header_dt );
4099 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4100 }
4101}

4103
4104static char*
4105icvGetFormat( const CvSeq* seq, const char* dt_key, CvAttrList* attr,
4106 int initial_elem_size, char* dt_buf )
4107{
4108 char* dt = 0;
4109 dt = (char*)cvAttrValue( attr, dt_key );
4110
4111 if( dt )
4112 {
4113 int dt_elem_size;
4114 dt_elem_size = icvCalcElemSize( dt, initial_elem_size );
4115 if( dt_elem_size != seq->elem_size )
4116 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
4117 "The size of element calculated from \"dt\" and "
4118 "the elem_size do not match" );
4119 }
4120 else if( CV_MAT_TYPE(seq->flags) != 0 || seq->elem_size == 1 )
4121 {
4122 if( CV_ELEM_SIZE(seq->flags) != seq->elem_size )
4123 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
4124 "Size of sequence element (elem_size) is inconsistent with seq->flags" );
4125 dt = icvEncodeFormat( CV_MAT_TYPE(seq->flags), dt_buf );
4126 }
4127 else if( seq->elem_size > initial_elem_size )
4128 {
4129 unsigned extra_elem_size = seq->elem_size - initial_elem_size;
4130 // a heuristic to provide nice defaults for sequences of int's & float's
4131 if( extra_elem_size % sizeof(int) == 0 )
4132 sprintf( dt_buf, "%ui", (unsigned)(extra_elem_size/sizeof(int)) );
4133 else
4134 sprintf( dt_buf, "%uu", extra_elem_size );
4135 dt = dt_buf;
4136 }
4137
4138 return dt;
4139}

4141
4142static void
4143icvWriteSeq( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* name,
4144 const void* struct_ptr,
4145 CvAttrList attr, int level )
4146{
4147 const CvSeq* seq = (CvSeq*)struct_ptr;
4148 CvSeqBlock* block;
4149 char buf[128];
4150 char dt_buf[128], *dt;
4151
4152 assert( CV_IS_SEQ( seq ));
4153 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, name, CV_NODE_MAP, CV_TYPE_NAME_SEQ );
4154
4155 if( level >= 0 )
4156 cvWriteInt( fs, "level", level );
4157
4158 dt = icvGetFormat( seq, "dt", &attr, 0, dt_buf );
4159
4160 strcpy(buf, "");
4161 if( CV_IS_SEQ_CLOSED(seq) )
4162 strcat(buf, " closed");
4163 if( CV_IS_SEQ_HOLE(seq) )
4164 strcat(buf, " hole");
4165 if( CV_IS_SEQ_CURVE(seq) )
4166 strcat(buf, " curve");
4167 if( CV_SEQ_ELTYPE(seq) == 0 && seq->elem_size != 1 )
4168 strcat(buf, " untyped");
4169
4170 cvWriteString( fs, "flags", buf + (buf[0] ? 1 : 0), 1 );
4171
4172 cvWriteInt( fs, "count", seq->total );
4173
4174 cvWriteString( fs, "dt", dt, 0 );
4175
4176 icvWriteHeaderData( fs, seq, &attr, sizeof(CvSeq) );
4177 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "data", CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );
4178
4179 for( block = seq->first; block; block = block->next )
4180 {
4181 cvWriteRawData( fs, block->data, block->count, dt );
4182 if( block == seq->first->prev )
4183 break;
4184 }
4185 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4186 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4187}

4190static void
4191icvWriteSeqTree( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* name,
4192 const void* struct_ptr, CvAttrList attr )
4193{
4194 const CvSeq* seq = (CvSeq*)struct_ptr;
4195 const char* recursive_value = cvAttrValue( &attr, "recursive" );
4196 int is_recursive = recursive_value &&
4197 strcmp(recursive_value,"0") != 0 &&
4198 strcmp(recursive_value,"false") != 0 &&
4199 strcmp(recursive_value,"False") != 0 &&
4200 strcmp(recursive_value,"FALSE") != 0;
4201
4202 assert( CV_IS_SEQ( seq ));
4203
4204 if( !is_recursive )
4205 {
4206 icvWriteSeq( fs, name, seq, attr, -1 );
4207 }
4208 else
4209 {
4210 CvTreeNodeIterator tree_iterator;
4211
4212 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, name, CV_NODE_MAP, CV_TYPE_NAME_SEQ_TREE );
4213 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, "sequences", CV_NODE_SEQ );
4214 cvInitTreeNodeIterator( &tree_iterator, seq, INT_MAX );
4215
4216 for(;;)
4217 {
4218 if( !tree_iterator.node )
4219 break;
4220 icvWriteSeq( fs, 0, tree_iterator.node, attr, tree_iterator.level );
4221 cvNextTreeNode( &tree_iterator );
4222 }
4223
4224 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4225 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4226 }
4227}

4229
4230static void*
4231icvReadSeq( CvFileStorage* fs, CvFileNode* node )
4232{
4233 void* ptr = 0;
4234 CvSeq* seq;
4235 CvSeqBlock* block;
4236 CvFileNode *data, *header_node, *rect_node, *origin_node;
4237 CvSeqReader reader;
4238 int total, flags;
4239 int elem_size, header_size = sizeof(CvSeq);
4240 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS], i, fmt_pair_count;
4241 int items_per_elem = 0;
4242 const char* flags_str;
4243 const char* header_dt;
4244 const char* dt;
4245 char* endptr = 0;
4246
4247 flags_str = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "flags", 0 );
4248 total = cvReadIntByName( fs, node, "count", -1 );
4249 dt = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "dt", 0 );
4250
4251 if( !flags_str || total == -1 || !dt )
4252 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Some of essential sequence attributes are absent" );
4253
4254 flags = CV_SEQ_MAGIC_VAL;
4255
4256 if( cv_isdigit(flags_str[0]) )
4257 {
4258 const int OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS = 9;
4259 const int OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_MASK = (1 << OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS) - 1;
4260 const int OLD_SEQ_KIND_BITS = 3;
4261 const int OLD_SEQ_KIND_MASK = ((1 << OLD_SEQ_KIND_BITS) - 1) << OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS;
4262 const int OLD_SEQ_KIND_CURVE = 1 << OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS;
4263 const int OLD_SEQ_FLAG_SHIFT = OLD_SEQ_KIND_BITS + OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS;
4264 const int OLD_SEQ_FLAG_CLOSED = 1 << OLD_SEQ_FLAG_SHIFT;
4265 const int OLD_SEQ_FLAG_HOLE = 8 << OLD_SEQ_FLAG_SHIFT;
4266
4267 int flags0 = (int)strtol( flags_str, &endptr, 16 );
4268 if( endptr == flags_str || (flags0 & CV_MAGIC_MASK) != CV_SEQ_MAGIC_VAL )
4269 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The sequence flags are invalid" );
4270 if( (flags0 & OLD_SEQ_KIND_MASK) == OLD_SEQ_KIND_CURVE )
4271 flags |= CV_SEQ_KIND_CURVE;
4272 if( flags0 & OLD_SEQ_FLAG_CLOSED )
4273 flags |= CV_SEQ_FLAG_CLOSED;
4274 if( flags0 & OLD_SEQ_FLAG_HOLE )
4275 flags |= CV_SEQ_FLAG_HOLE;
4276 flags |= flags0 & OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_MASK;
4277 }
4278 else
4279 {
4280 if( strstr(flags_str, "curve") )
4281 flags |= CV_SEQ_KIND_CURVE;
4282 if( strstr(flags_str, "closed") )
4283 flags |= CV_SEQ_FLAG_CLOSED;
4284 if( strstr(flags_str, "hole") )
4285 flags |= CV_SEQ_FLAG_HOLE;
4286 if( !strstr(flags_str, "untyped") )
4287 {
4288 try
4289 {
4290 flags |= icvDecodeSimpleFormat(dt);
4291 }
4292 catch(...)
4293 {
4294 }
4295 }
4296 }
4297
4298 header_dt = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "header_dt", 0 );
4299 header_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "header_user_data" );
4300
4301 if( (header_dt != 0) ^ (header_node != 0) )
4302 CV_Error( CV_StsError,
4303 "One of \"header_dt\" and \"header_user_data\" is there, while the other is not" );
4304
4305 rect_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "rect" );
4306 origin_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "origin" );
4307
4308 if( (header_node != 0) + (rect_node != 0) + (origin_node != 0) > 1 )
4309 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Only one of \"header_user_data\", \"rect\" and \"origin\" tags may occur" );
4310
4311 if( header_dt )
4312 {
4313 header_size = icvCalcElemSize( header_dt, header_size );
4314 }
4315 else if( rect_node )
4316 header_size = sizeof(CvPoint2DSeq);
4317 else if( origin_node )
4318 header_size = sizeof(CvChain);
4319
4320 elem_size = icvCalcElemSize( dt, 0 );
4321 seq = cvCreateSeq( flags, header_size, elem_size, fs->dststorage );
4322
4323 if( header_node )
4324 {
4325 cvReadRawData( fs, header_node, (char*)seq + sizeof(CvSeq), header_dt );
4326 }
4327 else if( rect_node )
4328 {
4329 CvPoint2DSeq* point_seq = (CvPoint2DSeq*)seq;
4330 point_seq->rect.x = cvReadIntByName( fs, rect_node, "x", 0 );
4331 point_seq->rect.y = cvReadIntByName( fs, rect_node, "y", 0 );
4332 point_seq->rect.width = cvReadIntByName( fs, rect_node, "width", 0 );
4333 point_seq->rect.height = cvReadIntByName( fs, rect_node, "height", 0 );
4334 point_seq->color = cvReadIntByName( fs, node, "color", 0 );
4335 }
4336 else if( origin_node )
4337 {
4338 CvChain* chain = (CvChain*)seq;
4339 chain->origin.x = cvReadIntByName( fs, origin_node, "x", 0 );
4340 chain->origin.y = cvReadIntByName( fs, origin_node, "y", 0 );
4341 }
4342
4343 cvSeqPushMulti( seq, 0, total, 0 );
4344 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( dt, fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
4345 fmt_pair_count *= 2;
4346 for( i = 0; i < fmt_pair_count; i += 2 )
4347 items_per_elem += fmt_pairs[i];
4348
4349 data = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "data" );
4350 if( !data )
4351 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The image data is not found in file storage" );
4352
4353 if( icvFileNodeSeqLen( data ) != total*items_per_elem )
4354 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The number of stored elements does not match to \"count\"" );
4355
4356 cvStartReadRawData( fs, data, &reader );
4357 for( block = seq->first; block; block = block->next )
4358 {
4359 int delta = block->count*items_per_elem;
4360 cvReadRawDataSlice( fs, &reader, delta, block->data, dt );
4361 if( block == seq->first->prev )
4362 break;
4363 }
4364
4365 ptr = seq;
4366 return ptr;
4367}

4369
4370static void*
4371icvReadSeqTree( CvFileStorage* fs, CvFileNode* node )
4372{
4373 void* ptr = 0;
4374 CvFileNode *sequences_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "sequences" );
4375 CvSeq* sequences;
4376 CvSeq* root = 0;
4377 CvSeq* parent = 0;
4378 CvSeq* prev_seq = 0;
4379 CvSeqReader reader;
4380 int i, total;
4381 int prev_level = 0;
4382
4383 if( !sequences_node || !CV_NODE_IS_SEQ(sequences_node->tag) )
4384 CV_Error( CV_StsParseError,
4385 "opencv-sequence-tree instance should contain a field \"sequences\" that should be a sequence" );
4386
4387 sequences = sequences_node->data.seq;
4388 total = sequences->total;
4389
4390 cvStartReadSeq( sequences, &reader, 0 );
4391 for( i = 0; i < total; i++ )
4392 {
4393 CvFileNode* elem = (CvFileNode*)reader.ptr;
4394 CvSeq* seq;
4395 int level;
4396 seq = (CvSeq*)cvRead( fs, elem );
4397 level = cvReadIntByName( fs, elem, "level", -1 );
4398 if( level < 0 )
4399 CV_Error( CV_StsParseError, "All the sequence tree nodes should contain \"level\" field" );
4400 if( !root )
4401 root = seq;
4402 if( level > prev_level )
4403 {
4404 assert( level == prev_level + 1 );
4405 parent = prev_seq;
4406 prev_seq = 0;
4407 if( parent )
4408 parent->v_next = seq;
4409 }
4410 else if( level < prev_level )
4411 {
4412 for( ; prev_level > level; prev_level-- )
4413 prev_seq = prev_seq->v_prev;
4414 parent = prev_seq->v_prev;
4415 }
4416 seq->h_prev = prev_seq;
4417 if( prev_seq )
4418 prev_seq->h_next = seq;
4419 seq->v_prev = parent;
4420 prev_seq = seq;
4421 prev_level = level;
4422 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( sequences->elem_size, reader );
4423 }
4424
4425 ptr = root;
4426 return ptr;
4427}

4454
4455static void
4456icvWriteGraph( CvFileStorage* fs, const char* name,
4457 const void* struct_ptr, CvAttrList attr )
4458{
4459 int* flag_buf = 0;
4460 char* write_buf = 0;
4461 const CvGraph* graph = (const CvGraph*)struct_ptr;
4462 CvSeqReader reader;
4463 char buf[128];
4464 int i, k, vtx_count, edge_count;
4465 char vtx_dt_buf[128], *vtx_dt;
4466 char edge_dt_buf[128], *edge_dt;
4467 int write_buf_size;
4468
4469 assert( CV_IS_GRAPH(graph) );
4470 vtx_count = cvGraphGetVtxCount( graph );
4471 edge_count = cvGraphGetEdgeCount( graph );
4472 flag_buf = (int*)cvAlloc( vtx_count*sizeof(flag_buf[0]));
4473
4474 // count vertices
4475 cvStartReadSeq( (CvSeq*)graph, &reader );
4476 for( i = 0, k = 0; i < graph->total; i++ )
4477 {
4478 if( CV_IS_SET_ELEM( reader.ptr ))
4479 {
4480 CvGraphVtx* vtx = (CvGraphVtx*)reader.ptr;
4481 flag_buf[k] = vtx->flags;
4482 vtx->flags = k++;
4483 }
4484 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( graph->elem_size, reader );
4485 }
4486
4487 // write header
4488 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, name, CV_NODE_MAP, CV_TYPE_NAME_GRAPH );
4489
4490 cvWriteString(fs, "flags", CV_IS_GRAPH_ORIENTED(graph) ? "oriented" : "", 1);
4491
4492 cvWriteInt( fs, "vertex_count", vtx_count );
4493 vtx_dt = icvGetFormat( (CvSeq*)graph, "vertex_dt",
4494 &attr, sizeof(CvGraphVtx), vtx_dt_buf );
4495 if( vtx_dt )
4496 cvWriteString( fs, "vertex_dt", vtx_dt, 0 );
4497
4498 cvWriteInt( fs, "edge_count", edge_count );
4499 edge_dt = icvGetFormat( (CvSeq*)graph->edges, "edge_dt",
4500 &attr, sizeof(CvGraphEdge), buf );
4501 sprintf( edge_dt_buf, "2if%s", edge_dt ? edge_dt : "" );
4502 edge_dt = edge_dt_buf;
4503 cvWriteString( fs, "edge_dt", edge_dt, 0 );
4504
4505 icvWriteHeaderData( fs, (CvSeq*)graph, &attr, sizeof(CvGraph) );
4506
4507 write_buf_size = MAX( 3*graph->elem_size, 1 << 16 );
4508 write_buf_size = MAX( 3*graph->edges->elem_size, write_buf_size );
4509 write_buf = (char*)cvAlloc( write_buf_size );
4510
4511 // as vertices and edges are written in similar way,
4512 // do it as a parametrized 2-iteration loop
4513 for( k = 0; k < 2; k++ )
4514 {
4515 const char* dt = k == 0 ? vtx_dt : edge_dt;
4516 if( dt )
4517 {
4518 CvSet* data = k == 0 ? (CvSet*)graph : graph->edges;
4519 int elem_size = data->elem_size;
4520 int write_elem_size = icvCalcElemSize( dt, 0 );
4521 char* src_ptr = write_buf;
4522 int write_max = write_buf_size / write_elem_size, write_count = 0;
4523
4524 // alignment of user part of the edge data following 2if
4525 int edge_user_align = sizeof(float);
4526
4527 if( k == 1 )
4528 {
4529 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS], fmt_pair_count;
4530 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( dt, fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
4531 if( fmt_pair_count > 2 && CV_ELEM_SIZE(fmt_pairs[2*2+1]) >= (int)sizeof(double))
4532 edge_user_align = sizeof(double);
4533 }
4534
4535 cvStartWriteStruct( fs, k == 0 ? "vertices" : "edges",
4536 CV_NODE_SEQ + CV_NODE_FLOW );
4537 cvStartReadSeq( (CvSeq*)data, &reader );
4538 for( i = 0; i < data->total; i++ )
4539 {
4540 if( CV_IS_SET_ELEM( reader.ptr ))
4541 {
4542 if( k == 0 ) // vertices
4543 memcpy( src_ptr, reader.ptr + sizeof(CvGraphVtx), write_elem_size );
4544 else
4545 {
4546 CvGraphEdge* edge = (CvGraphEdge*)reader.ptr;
4547 src_ptr = (char*)cvAlignPtr( src_ptr, sizeof(int) );
4548 ((int*)src_ptr)[0] = edge->vtx[0]->flags;
4549 ((int*)src_ptr)[1] = edge->vtx[1]->flags;
4550 *(float*)(src_ptr + sizeof(int)*2) = edge->weight;
4551 if( elem_size > (int)sizeof(CvGraphEdge) )
4552 {
4553 char* src_ptr2 = (char*)cvAlignPtr( src_ptr + 2*sizeof(int)
4554 + sizeof(float), edge_user_align );
4555 memcpy( src_ptr2, edge + 1, elem_size - sizeof(CvGraphEdge) );
4556 }
4557 }
4558 src_ptr += write_elem_size;
4559 if( ++write_count >= write_max )
4560 {
4561 cvWriteRawData( fs, write_buf, write_count, dt );
4562 write_count = 0;
4563 src_ptr = write_buf;
4564 }
4565 }
4566 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( data->elem_size, reader );
4567 }
4568
4569 if( write_count > 0 )
4570 cvWriteRawData( fs, write_buf, write_count, dt );
4571 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4572 }
4573 }
4574
4575 cvEndWriteStruct( fs );
4576
4577 // final stage. restore the graph flags
4578 cvStartReadSeq( (CvSeq*)graph, &reader );
4579 vtx_count = 0;
4580 for( i = 0; i < graph->total; i++ )
4581 {
4582 if( CV_IS_SET_ELEM( reader.ptr ))
4583 ((CvGraphVtx*)reader.ptr)->flags = flag_buf[vtx_count++];
4584 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( graph->elem_size, reader );
4585 }
4586
4587 cvFree( &write_buf );
4588 cvFree( &flag_buf );
4589}

4591
4592static void*
4593icvReadGraph( CvFileStorage* fs, CvFileNode* node )
4594{
4595 void* ptr = 0;
4596 char* read_buf = 0;
4597 CvGraphVtx** vtx_buf = 0;
4598 CvGraph* graph;
4599 CvFileNode *header_node, *vtx_node, *edge_node;
4600 int flags, vtx_count, edge_count;
4601 int vtx_size = sizeof(CvGraphVtx), edge_size, header_size = sizeof(CvGraph);
4602 int src_vtx_size = 0, src_edge_size;
4603 int fmt_pairs[CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS], fmt_pair_count;
4604 int vtx_items_per_elem = 0, edge_items_per_elem = 0;
4605 int edge_user_align = sizeof(float);
4606 int read_buf_size;
4607 int i, k;
4608 const char* flags_str;
4609 const char* header_dt;
4610 const char* vtx_dt;
4611 const char* edge_dt;
4612 char* endptr = 0;
4613
4614 flags_str = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "flags", 0 );
4615 vtx_dt = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "vertex_dt", 0 );
4616 edge_dt = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "edge_dt", 0 );
4617 vtx_count = cvReadIntByName( fs, node, "vertex_count", -1 );
4618 edge_count = cvReadIntByName( fs, node, "edge_count", -1 );
4619
4620 if( !flags_str || vtx_count == -1 || edge_count == -1 || !edge_dt )
4621 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Some of essential graph attributes are absent" );
4622
4623 flags = CV_SET_MAGIC_VAL + CV_GRAPH;
4624
4625 if( isxdigit(flags_str[0]) )
4626 {
4627 const int OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS = 9;
4628 const int OLD_SEQ_KIND_BITS = 3;
4629 const int OLD_SEQ_FLAG_SHIFT = OLD_SEQ_KIND_BITS + OLD_SEQ_ELTYPE_BITS;
4630 const int OLD_GRAPH_FLAG_ORIENTED = 1 << OLD_SEQ_FLAG_SHIFT;
4631
4632 int flags0 = (int)strtol( flags_str, &endptr, 16 );
4633 if( endptr == flags_str || (flags0 & CV_MAGIC_MASK) != CV_SET_MAGIC_VAL )
4634 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "The sequence flags are invalid" );
4635 if( flags0 & OLD_GRAPH_FLAG_ORIENTED )
4636 flags |= CV_GRAPH_FLAG_ORIENTED;
4637 }
4638 else
4639 {
4640 if( strstr(flags_str, "oriented") )
4641 flags |= CV_GRAPH_FLAG_ORIENTED;
4642 }
4643
4644 header_dt = cvReadStringByName( fs, node, "header_dt", 0 );
4645 header_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "header_user_data" );
4646
4647 if( (header_dt != 0) ^ (header_node != 0) )
4648 CV_Error( CV_StsError,
4649 "One of \"header_dt\" and \"header_user_data\" is there, while the other is not" );
4650
4651 if( header_dt )
4652 header_size = icvCalcElemSize( header_dt, header_size );
4653
4654 if( vtx_dt )
4655 {
4656 src_vtx_size = icvCalcElemSize( vtx_dt, 0 );
4657 vtx_size = icvCalcElemSize( vtx_dt, vtx_size );
4658 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( edge_dt,
4659 fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
4660 fmt_pair_count *= 2;
4661 for( i = 0; i < fmt_pair_count; i += 2 )
4662 vtx_items_per_elem += fmt_pairs[i];
4663 }
4664
4665 {
4666 char dst_edge_dt_buf[128];
4667 const char* dst_edge_dt = 0;
4668
4669 fmt_pair_count = icvDecodeFormat( edge_dt,
4670 fmt_pairs, CV_FS_MAX_FMT_PAIRS );
4671 if( fmt_pair_count < 2 ||
4672 fmt_pairs[0] != 2 || fmt_pairs[1] != CV_32S ||
4673 fmt_pairs[2] < 1 || fmt_pairs[3] != CV_32F )
4674 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg,
4675 "Graph edges should start with 2 integers and a float" );
4676
4677 // alignment of user part of the edge data following 2if
4678 if( fmt_pair_count > 2 && CV_ELEM_SIZE(fmt_pairs[5]) >= (int)sizeof(double))
4679 edge_user_align = sizeof(double);
4680
4681 fmt_pair_count *= 2;
4682 for( i = 0; i < fmt_pair_count; i += 2 )
4683 edge_items_per_elem += fmt_pairs[i];
4684
4685 if( edge_dt[2] == 'f' || (edge_dt[2] == '1' && edge_dt[3] == 'f') )
4686 dst_edge_dt = edge_dt + 3 + cv_isdigit(edge_dt[2]);
4687 else
4688 {
4689 int val = (int)strtol( edge_dt + 2, &endptr, 10 );
4690 sprintf( dst_edge_dt_buf, "%df%s", val-1, endptr );
4691 dst_edge_dt = dst_edge_dt_buf;
4692 }
4693
4694 edge_size = icvCalcElemSize( dst_edge_dt, sizeof(CvGraphEdge) );
4695 src_edge_size = icvCalcElemSize( edge_dt, 0 );
4696 }
4697
4698 graph = cvCreateGraph( flags, header_size, vtx_size, edge_size, fs->dststorage );
4699
4700 if( header_node )
4701 cvReadRawData( fs, header_node, (char*)graph + sizeof(CvGraph), header_dt );
4702
4703 read_buf_size = MAX( src_vtx_size*3, 1 << 16 );
4704 read_buf_size = MAX( src_edge_size*3, read_buf_size );
4705 read_buf = (char*)cvAlloc( read_buf_size );
4706 vtx_buf = (CvGraphVtx**)cvAlloc( vtx_count * sizeof(vtx_buf[0]) );
4707
4708 vtx_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "vertices" );
4709 edge_node = cvGetFileNodeByName( fs, node, "edges" );
4710 if( !edge_node )
4711 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "No edges data" );
4712 if( vtx_dt && !vtx_node )
4713 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "No vertices data" );
4714
4715 // as vertices and edges are read in similar way,
4716 // do it as a parametrized 2-iteration loop
4717 for( k = 0; k < 2; k++ )
4718 {
4719 const char* dt = k == 0 ? vtx_dt : edge_dt;
4720 int elem_size = k == 0 ? vtx_size : edge_size;
4721 int src_elem_size = k == 0 ? src_vtx_size : src_edge_size;
4722 int items_per_elem = k == 0 ? vtx_items_per_elem : edge_items_per_elem;
4723 int elem_count = k == 0 ? vtx_count : edge_count;
4724 char* dst_ptr = read_buf;
4725 int read_max = read_buf_size /MAX(src_elem_size, 1), read_count = 0;
4726 CvSeqReader reader;
4727 if(dt)
4728 cvStartReadRawData( fs, k == 0 ? vtx_node : edge_node, &reader );
4729
4730 for( i = 0; i < elem_count; i++ )
4731 {
4732 if( read_count == 0 && dt )
4733 {
4734 int count = MIN( elem_count - i, read_max )*items_per_elem;
4735 cvReadRawDataSlice( fs, &reader, count, read_buf, dt );
4736 read_count = count;
4737 dst_ptr = read_buf;
4738 }
4739
4740 if( k == 0 )
4741 {
4742 CvGraphVtx* vtx;
4743 cvGraphAddVtx( graph, 0, &vtx );
4744 vtx_buf[i] = vtx;
4745 if( dt )
4746 memcpy( vtx + 1, dst_ptr, src_elem_size );
4747 }
4748 else
4749 {
4750 CvGraphEdge* edge = 0;
4751 int vtx1 = ((int*)dst_ptr)[0];
4752 int vtx2 = ((int*)dst_ptr)[1];
4753 int result;
4754
4755 if( (unsigned)vtx1 >= (unsigned)vtx_count ||
4756 (unsigned)vtx2 >= (unsigned)vtx_count )
4757 CV_Error( CV_StsOutOfRange,
4758 "Some of stored vertex indices are out of range" );
4759
4760 result = cvGraphAddEdgeByPtr( graph,
4761 vtx_buf[vtx1], vtx_buf[vtx2], 0, &edge );
4762
4763 if( result == 0 )
4764 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Duplicated edge has occured" );
4765
4766 edge->weight = *(float*)(dst_ptr + sizeof(int)*2);
4767 if( elem_size > (int)sizeof(CvGraphEdge) )
4768 {
4769 char* dst_ptr2 = (char*)cvAlignPtr( dst_ptr + sizeof(int)*2 +
4770 sizeof(float), edge_user_align );
4771 memcpy( edge + 1, dst_ptr2, elem_size - sizeof(CvGraphEdge) );
4772 }
4773 }
4774
4775 dst_ptr += src_elem_size;
4776 read_count--;
4777 }
4778 }
4779
4780 ptr = graph;
4781 cvFree( &read_buf );
4782 cvFree( &vtx_buf );
4783
4784 return ptr;
4785}

4842CV_IMPL void
4843cvRegisterType( const CvTypeInfo* _info )
4844{
4845 CvTypeInfo* info = 0;
4846 int i, len;
4847 char c;
4848
4849 //if( !CvType::first )
4850 // icvCreateStandardTypes();
4851
4852 if( !_info || _info->header_size != sizeof(CvTypeInfo) )
4853 CV_Error( CV_StsBadSize, "Invalid type info" );
4854
4855 if( !_info->is_instance || !_info->release ||
4856 !_info->read || !_info->write )
4857 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr,
4858 "Some of required function pointers "
4859 "(is_instance, release, read or write) are NULL");
4860
4861 c = _info->type_name[0];
4862 if( !cv_isalpha(c) && c != '_' )
4863 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg, "Type name should start with a letter or _" );
4864
4865 len = (int)strlen(_info->type_name);
4866
4867 for( i = 0; i < len; i++ )
4868 {
4869 c = _info->type_name[i];
4870 if( !cv_isalnum(c) && c != '-' && c != '_' )
4871 CV_Error( CV_StsBadArg,
4872 "Type name should contain only letters, digits, - and _" );
4873 }
4874
4875 info = (CvTypeInfo*)cvAlloc( sizeof(*info) + len + 1 );
4876
4877 *info = *_info;
4878 info->type_name = (char*)(info + 1);
4879 memcpy( (char*)info->type_name, _info->type_name, len + 1 );
4880
4881 info->flags = 0;
4882 info->next = CvType::first;
4883 info->prev = 0;
4884 if( CvType::first )
4885 CvType::first->prev = info;
4886 else
4887 CvType::last = info;
4888 CvType::first = info;
4889}

4892CV_IMPL void
4893cvUnregisterType( const char* type_name )
4894{
4895 CvTypeInfo* info;
4896
4897 info = cvFindType( type_name );
4898 if( info )
4899 {
4900 if( info->prev )
4901 info->prev->next = info->next;
4902 else
4903 CvType::first = info->next;
4904
4905 if( info->next )
4906 info->next->prev = info->prev;
4907 else
4908 CvType::last = info->prev;
4909
4910 if( !CvType::first || !CvType::last )
4911 CvType::first = CvType::last = 0;
4912
4913 cvFree( &info );
4914 }
4915}

5062
5063CV_IMPL void*
5064cvLoad( const char* filename, CvMemStorage* memstorage,
5065 const char* name, const char** _real_name )
5066{
5067 void* ptr = 0;
5068 const char* real_name = 0;
5069 cv::FileStorage fs(cvOpenFileStorage(filename, memstorage, CV_STORAGE_READ));
5070
5071 CvFileNode* node = 0;
5072
5073 if( !fs.isOpened() )
5074 return 0;
5075
5076 if( name )
5077 {
5078 node = cvGetFileNodeByName( *fs, 0, name );
5079 }
5080 else
5081 {
5082 int i, k;
5083 for( k = 0; k < (*fs)->roots->total; k++ )
5084 {
5085 CvSeq* seq;
5086 CvSeqReader reader;
5087
5088 node = (CvFileNode*)cvGetSeqElem( (*fs)->roots, k );
5089 if( !CV_NODE_IS_MAP( node->tag ))
5090 return 0;
5091 seq = node->data.seq;
5092 node = 0;
5093
5094 cvStartReadSeq( seq, &reader, 0 );
5095
5096 // find the first element in the map
5097 for( i = 0; i < seq->total; i++ )
5098 {
5099 if( CV_IS_SET_ELEM( reader.ptr ))
5100 {
5101 node = (CvFileNode*)reader.ptr;
5102 goto stop_search;
5103 }
5104 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( seq->elem_size, reader );
5105 }
5106 }
5107
5108stop_search:
5109 ;
5110 }
5111
5112 if( !node )
5113 CV_Error( CV_StsObjectNotFound, "Could not find the/an object in file storage" );
5114
5115 real_name = cvGetFileNodeName( node );
5116 ptr = cvRead( *fs, node, 0 );
5117
5118 // sanity check
5119 if( !memstorage && (CV_IS_SEQ( ptr ) || CV_IS_SET( ptr )) )
5120 CV_Error( CV_StsNullPtr,
5121 "NULL memory storage is passed - the loaded dynamic structure can not be stored" );
5122
5123 if( cvGetErrStatus() < 0 )
5124 {
5125 cvRelease( (void**)&ptr );
5126 real_name = 0;
5127 }
5128
5129 if( _real_name)
5130 {
5131 if (real_name)
5132 {
5133 *_real_name = (const char*)cvAlloc(strlen(real_name));
5134 memcpy((void*)*_real_name, real_name, strlen(real_name));
5135 } else {
5136 *_real_name = 0;
5137 }
5138 }
5139
5140 return ptr;
5141}

5148
5149static void getElemSize( const string& fmt, size_t& elemSize, size_t& cn )
5150{
5151 const char* dt = fmt.c_str();
5152 cn = 1;
5153 if( cv_isdigit(dt[0]) )
5154 {
5155 cn = dt[0] - '0';
5156 dt++;
5157 }
5158 char c = dt[0];
5159 elemSize = cn*(c == 'u' || c == 'c' ? sizeof(uchar) : c == 'w' || c == 's' ? sizeof(ushort) :
5160 c == 'i' ? sizeof(int) : c == 'f' ? sizeof(float) : c == 'd' ? sizeof(double) :
5161 c == 'r' ? sizeof(void*) : (size_t)0);
5162}

5227
5228FileStorage& operator << (FileStorage& fs, const string& str)
5229{
5230 enum { NAME_EXPECTED = FileStorage::NAME_EXPECTED,
5231 VALUE_EXPECTED = FileStorage::VALUE_EXPECTED,
5232 INSIDE_MAP = FileStorage::INSIDE_MAP };
5233 const char* _str = str.c_str();
5234 if( !fs.isOpened() || !_str )
5235 return fs;
5236 if( *_str == '}' || *_str == ']' )
5237 {
5238 if( fs.structs.empty() )
5239 CV_Error_( CV_StsError, ("Extra closing '%c'", *_str) );
5240 if( (*_str == ']' ? '[' : '{') != fs.structs.back() )
5241 CV_Error_( CV_StsError,
5242 ("The closing '%c' does not match the opening '%c'", *_str, fs.structs.back()));
5243 fs.structs.pop_back();
5244 fs.state = fs.structs.empty() || fs.structs.back() == '{' ?
5245 INSIDE_MAP + NAME_EXPECTED : VALUE_EXPECTED;
5246 cvEndWriteStruct( *fs );
5247 fs.elname = string();
5248 }
5249 else if( fs.state == NAME_EXPECTED + INSIDE_MAP )
5250 {
5251 if (!cv_isalpha(*_str) && *_str != '_')
5252 CV_Error_( CV_StsError, ("Incorrect element name %s", _str) );
5253 fs.elname = str;
5254 fs.state = VALUE_EXPECTED + INSIDE_MAP;
5255 }
5256 else if( (fs.state & 3) == VALUE_EXPECTED )
5257 {
5258 if( *_str == '{' || *_str == '[' )
5259 {
5260 fs.structs.push_back(*_str);
5261 int flags = *_str++ == '{' ? CV_NODE_MAP : CV_NODE_SEQ;
5262 fs.state = flags == CV_NODE_MAP ? INSIDE_MAP +
5263 NAME_EXPECTED : VALUE_EXPECTED;
5264 if( *_str == ':' )
5265 {
5266 flags |= CV_NODE_FLOW;
5267 _str++;
5268 }
5269 cvStartWriteStruct( *fs, fs.elname.size() > 0 ? fs.elname.c_str() : 0,
5270 flags, *_str ? _str : 0 );
5271 fs.elname = string();
5272 }
5273 else
5274 {
5275 write( fs, fs.elname, (_str[0] == '\\' && (_str[1] == '{' || _str[1] == '}' ||
5276 _str[1] == '[' || _str[1] == ']')) ? string(_str+1) : str );
5277 if( fs.state == INSIDE_MAP + VALUE_EXPECTED )
5278 fs.state = INSIDE_MAP + NAME_EXPECTED;
5279 }
5280 }
5281 else
5282 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "Invalid fs.state" );
5283 return fs;
5284}

5352
5353FileNodeIterator::FileNodeIterator(const CvFileStorage* _fs,
5354 const CvFileNode* _node, size_t _ofs)
5355{
5356 if( _fs && _node && CV_NODE_TYPE(_node->tag) != CV_NODE_NONE )
5357 {
5358 int node_type = _node->tag & FileNode::TYPE_MASK;
5359 fs = _fs;
5360 container = _node;
5361 if( !(_node->tag & FileNode::USER) && (node_type == FileNode::SEQ || node_type == FileNode::MAP) )
5362 {
5363 cvStartReadSeq( _node->data.seq, &reader );
5364 remaining = FileNode(_fs, _node).size();
5365 }
5366 else
5367 {
5368 reader.ptr = (schar*)_node;
5369 reader.seq = 0;
5370 remaining = 1;
5371 }
5372 (*this) += (int)_ofs;
5373 }
5374 else
5375 {
5376 fs = 0;
5377 container = 0;
5378 reader.ptr = 0;
5379 remaining = 0;
5380 }
5381}

5391FileNodeIterator& FileNodeIterator::operator ++()
5392{
5393 if( remaining > 0 )
5394 {
5395 if( reader.seq )
5396 CV_NEXT_SEQ_ELEM( reader.seq->elem_size, reader );
5397 remaining--;
5398 }
5399 return *this;
5400}

5402FileNodeIterator FileNodeIterator::operator ++(int)
5403{
5404 FileNodeIterator it = *this;
5405 ++(*this);
5406 return it;
5407}
5408
5409FileNodeIterator& FileNodeIterator::operator --()
5410{
5411 if( remaining < FileNode(fs, container).size() )
5412 {
5413 if( reader.seq )
5414 CV_PREV_SEQ_ELEM( reader.seq->elem_size, reader );
5415 remaining++;
5416 }
5417 return *this;
5418}
5419
5420FileNodeIterator FileNodeIterator::operator --(int)
5421{
5422 FileNodeIterator it = *this;
5423 --(*this);
5424 return it;
5425}
5426
5427FileNodeIterator& FileNodeIterator::operator += (int ofs)
5428{
5429 if( ofs == 0 )
5430 return *this;
5431 if( ofs > 0 )
5432 ofs = std::min(ofs, (int)remaining);
5433 else
5434 {
5435 size_t count = FileNode(fs, container).size();
5436 ofs = (int)(remaining - std::min(remaining - ofs, count));
5437 }
5438 remaining -= ofs;
5439 if( reader.seq )
5440 cvSetSeqReaderPos( &reader, ofs, 1 );
5441 return *this;
5442}
5443
5444FileNodeIterator& FileNodeIterator::operator -= (int ofs)
5445{
5446 return operator += (-ofs);
5447}

5449
5450FileNodeIterator& FileNodeIterator::readRaw( const string& fmt, uchar* vec, size_t maxCount )
5451{
5452 if( fs && container && remaining > 0 )
5453 {
5454 size_t elem_size, cn;
5455 getElemSize( fmt, elem_size, cn );
5456 CV_Assert( elem_size > 0 );
5457 size_t count = std::min(remaining, maxCount);
5458
5459 if( reader.seq )
5460 {
5461 cvReadRawDataSlice( fs, &reader, (int)count, vec, fmt.c_str() );
5462 remaining -= count*cn;
5463 }
5464 else
5465 {
5466 cvReadRawData( fs, container, vec, fmt.c_str() );
5467 remaining = 0;
5468 }
5469 }
5470 return *this;
5471}

5531void read( const FileNode& node, Mat& mat, const Mat& default_mat )
5532{
5533 if( node.empty() )
5534 {
5535 default_mat.copyTo(mat);
5536 return;
5537 }
5538 void* obj = cvRead((CvFileStorage*)node.fs, (CvFileNode*)*node);
5539 if(CV_IS_MAT_HDR_Z(obj))
5540 {
5541 Mat((const CvMat*)obj).copyTo(mat);
5542 cvReleaseMat((CvMat**)&obj);
5543 }
5544 else if(CV_IS_MATND_HDR(obj))
5545 {
5546 Mat((const CvMatND*)obj).copyTo(mat);
5547 cvReleaseMatND((CvMatND**)&obj);
5548 }
5549 else
5550 {
5551 cvRelease(&obj);
5552 CV_Error(CV_StsBadArg, "Unknown array type");
5553 }
5554}
5555
5556void read( const FileNode& node, SparseMat& mat, const SparseMat& default_mat )
5557{
5558 if( node.empty() )
5559 {
5560 default_mat.copyTo(mat);
5561 return;
5562 }
5563 Ptr<CvSparseMat> m = (CvSparseMat*)cvRead((CvFileStorage*)node.fs, (CvFileNode*)*node);
5564 CV_Assert(CV_IS_SPARSE_MAT(m));
5565 SparseMat(m).copyTo(mat);
5566}
